(235, 'en', 'VNEEP launches two green building contests', 'HCMC – The Vietnamese National Energy Efficiency Program (VNEEP) has launched two contests that aim to encourage local businesses, architects and construction designers to develop green buildings.', 'upload/images/235.jpg', '2010-05-07', '<p>The ministries of Construction and Industry and Trade sponsored the scheme, which was launched on Thursday at the Caravelle Hotel. </p><p>The 4th Energy Efficiency Building 2010 contest has been organized by the HCMC Energy Conservation Center (EEC-HCMC) and aims to honor construction projects that efficiently use energy via state-of-the-art management systems. </p><p>Huynh Kim Tuoc, director of the center, said that, “This contest is an occasion to honor the owners, architects and consulting and designing firms, who have created green buildings, and also to find new models and recommend them to investors”. </p><p>He added that all relevant information concerning the contest is on their website at <a href=\"http://www.eec-hcm.gov.vn/\">www.eec-hcm.gov.vn</a>.</p><p>“More than 100 buildings submitted applications to take part in the three previous contests, but we accepted only 73 valid applications and just 33 were given awards and certificates,” he said.</p><p>He added that this year he expected the contest to attract about 30 applications; however, only six will be chosen for the contest organized by the ASEAN Energy Center. </p><p>Also at the ceremony, Hoang Minh Lam, a Hanoi City Energy Conservation Center representative, introduced the Energy Management in Industry and Buildings contest, which will be extended to the entire country for the first time.&nbsp; </p><p>“All contestants will have opportunities to receive consultation on energy auditing, integration of energy management systems and energy saving technology,” Lam said, adding that the contest will help develop a green economy in Vietnam and increase prestige especially among sensitive export markets like North America, the EU and Japan. </p><p>Contestants can visit <a href=\"http://www.eechanoi.gov.vn/\">www.eechanoi.gov.vn</a> for details.</p>', 71, 197, 1, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(236, 'en', 'Heavy polluters still spared from criminal proceedings', 'HCMC – The environment authorities still have difficulty taking criminal proceedings against environment polluters due to the lack of necessary regulations stipulated in the criminal law, said the director of the Vietnam Environment Administration’s Institute of Science for Environmental Management.', '', '2010-05-11', '<p>Pham Van Loi said that while many enterprises were still causing serious pollution, the penal code still hindered criminal proceedings against pollution-causing businesses. </p><p>“If any enterprise is discovered causing heavy pollution, the leader of that enterprise could be criminally charged to increase deterrence, but unfortunately, the penal code does not establish criminal responsibility of an individual,” he told the Daily on the sidelines of a seminar on new regulations for environment protection in HCMC on Monday. </p><p>Loi did admit that the newly-issued regulations for environment protection were enough to encourage enterprises, organizations and individuals to keep the environment clean. </p><p>However, several enterprises are still lacking respect for the environment with some of them guilty of concealing violations, including Vedan, Tung Kuang Joint Stock Company and Quang Ngai Sugar Joint Stock Company. </p><p>The director of the Institute of Science for Environmental Management also recommended that since an increasing number of heavy polluters were found, related agencies should ask the National Assembly to include individual responsibility for heavy pollution in the penal code.&nbsp;&nbsp; </p><p>Pham Van Nghiem, an official of the HCMC Health Department, told on Monday’s seminar that with increasing violations of environment protection law, people’s health had been negatively affected, particularly with the worsening air pollution and contamination of most of the city’s waterways. </p><p>Since early this year, the city’s Department of Natural Resources and Environment has fined 100 enterprises a total of VND600 million for violations. </p><p>HCMC’s environmental authorities recently discovered Thu Duc Steel Company in Thu Duc District discharging over 10,000 tons of untreated iron residues into the environment. </p><p>According to an official of the city’s Department of Natural Resources and Environment, after discovering Thu Duc Steel Company discharging the residues in Phuoc Long A Ward of District 9, related agencies on Monday&nbsp;started taking samples for testing to determine whether these is harmful waste. </p><p>“The city’s environment authorities will impose heavy fines on the company&nbsp;according to the new regulations if the discharged residues are found to be harmful industrial waste,” said the official.</p>', 71, 228, 1, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(237, 'en', 'Aquatic animals helpless against electrofishing', 'HCMC - Fish, shrimp and many other kinds of aquatic animals living in waterways of Vietnam’s southern provinces have been seriously reduced by illegal electrofishing, according to the HCMC Agency for Protecting Aquatic Product Sources.', 'upload/images/237.jpg', '2010-05-13', '<p>“After ten recent inspections in HCMC and nearby provinces, the inspectors discovered 455 violations of catching fish by electricity. This causes a serious decline of the aquatic products in the region’s waterways,” said Dang Van Thuan of the agency. </p><p>Thuan told the Daily on Tuesday that in HCMC the agency had found many violations on fishing by electricity in suburban districts such as Can Gio, Cu Chi and Binh Chanh. </p><p>He said catching fish by electricity was feared to exterminate most aquatic animals in the near future because fish, shrimp, frogs and others are left floating on the surface in a twinkling after they are stunned by electricity. </p><p>The method uses a transformer to pulse current from a battery or power generator before the current is delivered into the water to stun the fish. </p><p>Thuan said that to control the increase of illegal electrofishing in the region the agency had been coordinating with ten southern provinces for overall inspections from May 6 to on Wednesday. </p><p>He also said after a preliminary report of the one-week inspection that 135 other cases of illegal fishing had been found, including many violations for electrofishing. </p><p>According to the agency, related agencies in the region need to encourage and support local people, especially the poor, to stop electrofishing and to breed more freshwater animals to keep them in existence.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p><p>According to a Government decree which was issued in March and takes effect on Saturday,&nbsp;any violation in illegal electrofishing will be fined from VND2 million to VND20 million.</p>', 71, 51, 1, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(238, 'en', 'Cranes Get Into Murky Water', 'Recently, forest fires at Tram Chim National Park have provoked public outcries. The following are arguments by two scientists about this issue. Both have spent a long time doing research at this park.', '', '2010-05-19', '<span class=\"Content\" id=\"ctl00_cphContent_lblContentHtml\">	<p>There are different ecosystems in Tram Chim National Park due to the accumulation of organic substances in different areas of the park. Therefore, forest fires in Tram Chim would lead to varying effects on the local biological diversification whose conclusion requires a comprehensive evaluation.<br />		Observations conducted since 1995 at the park show that a fire on a community of cajeput can cause death to 80% of the trees if they are between one and five years old, about 50% of the trees if they are aged 6-10, and 20% of them if the trees live longer than 11 years. Notably, all the area destroyed by fires will recover naturally after three or four years.<br />		Different from the cajeput ecosystem, the remaining ones such as those of Chinese water chestnut (Eleocharis dulcis), brownbeard rice and bent quickly come to life again only after three or four months. Saurus cranes, called locally as su u (literally red-headed crane), often feed on burned out Chinese water chestnut fields. Because the top soil of biomass has disappeared due to fire, the cranes find it easy to dig for the tubers beneath.<br />		Just like the local fauna, local people have learned how to exploit efficiently the biological diversity in the dry season in Dong Thap Muoi area where Tram Chim National Park is located. During the dry season they catch fish and shrimp in deep or running water. For this reason, when the hot season comes to an end, local people always set fire to the fields to either hunt for birds or rats, or clear away the grass so that it will be easier for them to spread fishing net or set bamboo fish traps in the coming flood season.<br />		The local habit of setting fire to the fields partly helps reduce the accumulation of organic substances on the top soil. To local residents, fire is the quickest and cheapest way to clean the fields. This practice is still applied in various places.</p>	<p class=\"SGTOSubTitle\">Inappropriate fire prevention</p>	<p>In 1990, to keep water in the dry season, Tram Chim National Park authorities had a system of dike and water-regulating culvert built. This system—similar to the half-high dike, also referred to as the August dike in An Giang and Long An Provinces’ rice fields—prevents floodwater until August. Afterwards, flood will overflow the bank and submerge the whole park.</p>	<p>To prevent forest fires, since 1999 the park authorities have kept much water in the dry season. In 2002, the dike system was raised higher so that water inside the park was retained at a high level, and water from outside could not overflow the bank during the flood season. This system has caused a host of changes to the park’s ecosystem. First, it cuts the quantity of fish migrating into Tram Chim during the flood season. It also limits the water flow between areas in- and outside the park, which spurs a bigger accumulation of organic substances. At the same time, as it is an anaerobic process, it causes more pollution to the water.</p>	<p>The higher water level has killed off many fields of Chinese water chestnut or their tubers, which in turn reduces food for Saurus cranes and thus the number of cranes returning to the park. Although much has been done to adjust the water level and recover the Chinese water chestnut fields, the number of Saurus cranes returning to the national park remains modest.</p>	<p>Every year, each hectare of grass field in Tram Chim park produces some 20 tons of organic substances, and each hectare of cajeput about 12 tons. Previously, when the national park was not yet established, accumulated organic substances were mostly cleaned by fires set by local residents and the remainder was swept away by floodwater. Organic substance accumulation on the fields was insignificant.</p>	<p>Currently, such accumulation has rendered water management in the national park more complicated. Excessive water kills grass, causes more pollution, reduces the number of fish schools and Chinese water chestnut tubers as well as Saurus cranes. On the contrary, if the water level is lowered, the risk of forest fires will increase. Fires are likely to change the ecosystems and provoke public outcries. However, if the area destroyed by forest fires is less than 30% of the total, it will not necessarily damage biological diversity.</p>	<p>In short, the protection of the national park’s ecosystem is one involving both water and fire. Either too much of water or fire will affect biological diversity. But it is also noteworthy that retaining excessive water will accelerate the accumulation of organic substances, and the damage to biological diversity due to excessive amount of water is more difficult to deal with. Saurus cranes shunning the park are just an exemplification.</p></span>', 71, 70, 1, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(239, 'en', 'Vietnam intensifies pollution control at industrial parks', 'HCMC – The Environment Administration has asked all provincial departments of natural resources and environment to intensify environmental pollution control at all economic zones, hi-tech parks and industrial parks. ', '', '2010-05-20', '<p>Le Ke Son, deputy director of the administration, said in a document sent these departments nationwide that actions for environment protection at industrial parks were inadequate while provincial environmental authorities were not stern enough in dealing with the polluters. </p><p>Son said the untreated industrial wastewater, waste and smoke at many industrial parks were causing serious pollution for surrounding communities and affecting health as well as causing great concerns among the public. </p><p>The administration also required the departments to prioritize the problem this year. This means stronger penalties on heavy polluters or even suspension of production activities of any polluting enterprise. </p><p>According to the Ministry of Planning and Investment, as of the end of 2009, the country had some 250 registered industrial parks with a total land area of some 63,200 hectares.</p>', 71, 199, 1, 1, 'vietnam', NULL, NULL),
(240, 'en', 'Experts warn of risks as dollar loans rise rapidly', 'HCMC – Several experts have voiced concerns over the tendency of corporate borrowers taking out more loans in the U.S. dollar, saying this poses risks of forex fluctuations in the future.', 'upload/images/240.jpg', '2010-05-13', '<p>The lending rate for dollar loans is much lower than that for Vietnam dong funds, averaging out at 7%-8% and 14%-15% respectively. This wide differential encourages corporate borrowers to apply for more dollar loans these days.</p><p>Vo Tri Thanh, deputy director of the Central Institute for Economic Management, told the Daily that borrowing U.S. dollar this time around was good for enterprises due to lower rates, but when those loans were due, demand to buy dollars for loan repayment would surge in the future.</p><p>“Any failure to balance dollar demand and supply on the part of banks would affect the foreign exchange market and the whole economy,” he explained. </p><p>Le Xuan Nghia, vice chairman of the National Financial Supervisory Commission, said in local media that negative market movements could occur if the tendency continued.</p><p>“Since early this year, dollar mobilization by banks has slowed and even declined while outstanding loans in dollar have continued to rise,” he said, adding this would exert pressure on interest rates for the dollar. </p><p>“Enterprises borrowing the dollar should think of forex rate insurance to prevent risks. Meanwhile, banks should not chase short-term profit to increase lending in the dollar,” Nghia said. </p><p>Pham Duy Hung, CEO of Asia Vietnam Commercial Bank, said that although there were some warnings for corporate dollar borrowers, many still preferred dollar loans. They think that the central bank has committed to keep the forex rate stable so the Vietnamese dong might not be devalued as much as the difference between lending rates for the two currencies, he said. </p><p>Banks said mobilization in the dollar had recently subsided compared to the early months of the year. </p><p>A leader of a joint-stock company said recently dollar mobilization tended to slow because depositors predicted that the forex rate would not change too much so they did not buy and deposit dollars. </p><p>The State Bank of Vietnam in its April report revealed that dollar mobilization had registered slower growth at a mere 0.78% from March while dollar credit growth was 3%. </p><p>Earlier, dollar raising grew 1.02% in March and dollar credit growth was up 3.98%. For the first quarter this year alone, dollar funds streaming into banks rose only 0.21% compared to late last year and credit growth in the foreign currency was up 14.07%. </p><p>For that reason, the central bank has asked banks to make reports on mobilization and outstanding loans in the dollar as well as ensure safety when giving dollar loans.</p>', 72, 284, 1, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(241, 'en', 'Gold prices surge to over VND28 million', 'HCMC – Local gold prices continued to soar following the world trend on Wednesday, rising VND660,000 from the previous day to VND28.1 million and VND28.3 million per tael for buying and selling, according to Saigon Jewelry Holding Co. (SJC).', 'upload/images/241.jpg', '2010-05-13', '<p>Meanwhile, Hanoi-based Bao Tin Minh Chau Co. bought and sold the precious metal at VND28 million and VND28.13 million per tael respectively on Wednesday.</p><p>Retail gold shops widened the gap between buying and selling prices to cope with strong price fluctuations. </p><p>Traders did not want to buy gold at such high prices, according to a gold shop owner at An Dong Market.</p><p>Investors also stopped selling gold on Wednesday as the world price was expected to soar to US$1,250 an ounce in the near future. </p><p>Trading at large enterprises and retail shops remained normal throughout the day.</p><p>Nguyen Cong Tuong, SJC deputy marketing director, said that his firm bought 4,000 gold taels and sold 1,000 taels on Wednesday while Bao Tin Minh Chau Co. had only a few transactions, as investors were cautious due to the price hike.</p><p>Meanwhile, Phu Nhuan Jewelry Co. (PNJ) bought 3,600 gold taels on Wednesday, increasing by around 20% from previous days while its selling volume remained low. </p><p>Nguyen Thi Cuc, PNJ deputy general director, said that people raced to offload gold in the morning but decreased their selling later.</p><p>Sacombank Jewelry Co. has reported steady growth rates of gold buying volume over the past two weeks. It buys around 8,000 gold taels and sells 5,000 taels each day.</p><p>On the European market, gold prices continued to increase, rising US$9.9 an ounce to close at US$1,241 at 5:00 p.m. on Wednesday.</p><p>Vietcombank on Wednesday quoted the dollar at VND18,990 and VND19,050 for buying and selling respectively. On the unofficial market, the greenback was bought and sold at VND19,050 and VND19,150.</p>', 72, 324, 1, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(242, 'en', 'Gold buying power increases', ' HCMC – Residents’ gold buying power has increased strongly recently as the precious metal is considered a safe bet against economic uncertainty.', '', '2010-05-14', '<p>omestic gold prices increased by over VND1.6 million per tael on Thursday, or 5.3%, against late last month. However, enterprises continue to buy gold in bulk, even though buying power is still modest. 	<img align=\"right\" src=\"http://english.thesaigontimes.vn/App_Themes/Default/Imgs/SGTO_ADVERTISING.jpg\" alt=\"Vị trí đặt quảng cáo\" class=\"SGTOADV\" /></p><p>Saigon Jewelry Holding Co. (SJC) has strongly raised its buying power this month, purchasing around 4,000 gold taels per day, double compared to April, after the world price hit US$1,200 an ounce on May 6. The enterprise bought around 10,000 taels as local gold prices reached over VND28 million per tael this Monday.</p><p>SJC deputy marketing director Nguyen Cong Tuong said residents had increased their selling power as banks demanded to balance gold accounts. “People did not rush to invest in gold due to fears of a price reversion,” Tuong said.</p><p>Meanwhile, Sacombank Jewelry Co. (SBJ) has bought around 8,000 taels and sold 5,000 taels each day since early this month. Nguyen Ngoc Que Chi, SBJ’s general director, said, “Gold prices have risen due to high material demands for jewelry production, not due to speculation.” </p><p>Local gold traders also said that local price hikes followed the global market. “Gold trading in the country is normal currently and there is no gold shortage on the market,” Tuong added.</p><p>Speculation caused gold prices in Vietnam to skyrocket last November as the central bank prohibited gold import and the dollar strongly appreciated. Nguyen Thi Cuc, deputy general director of Phu Nhuan Jewelry Co., said that local gold prices are now lower than the world’s and the currency market is stable. As a result, speculators cannot influence prices. </p><p>SJC quoted gold prices at VND28.07 million and VND28.17 million for buying and selling respectively, decreasing by VND30,000 from the previous day. Gold fell US$4 to US$1,233 an ounce.</p><p>The U.S. dollar on the unofficial market inched up VND50 to VND19,150 and VND19,200 for buying and selling respectively.</p>', 72, 269, 1, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(243, 'en', 'SBV rejects devaluation, says dollar funds ample', 'HCMC – The State Bank of Vietnam on Thursday brushed off rumors over a sharp devaluation of Vietnam dong, saying the economy is still awash with dollar funds with ever-increasing greenback sales by commercial banks.', '', '2010-05-14', '<span class=\"Content\" id=\"ctl00_cphContent_lblContentHtml\">	<p class=\"SGTOContent\">The central bank since the middle of April has bought a total of US$1 billion from credit institutions to increase the country’s foreign reserves, SBV said in a statement on its website on Thursday.		<img align=\"right\" src=\"http://english.thesaigontimes.vn/App_Themes/Default/Imgs/SGTO_ADVERTISING.jpg\" alt=\"Vị trí đặt quảng cáo\" class=\"SGTOADV\" /></p>	<p>The central bank said since late March, the foreign exchange market had become calm with fairly plentiful dollar supply while legal demands for the U.S. dollar of individuals and institutions had all been met. </p>	<p>Recently, there has been a rumor that Vietnam dong will be strongly devalued against the U.S. dollar for many reasons, including that many enterprises have shifted to taking out loans in the U.S. dollar that would lead to a surge in dollar demand in the future. </p>	<p>Meanwhile, there has been concern that the U.S. dollar would continue rising against other currencies, which coupled with Vietnam’s ballooning trade deficit will exert more pressure on Vietnam dong. </p>	<p>Tran Hoang Ngan, member of the Advisory Board for National Monetary Policy and vice principal of the HCMC University of Economics, remarked that dollar speculation had declined given a big difference between interest rates in the U.S. dollar and Vietnam dong. </p>	<p>“Recently, if there were not intervention by the central bank, the U.S. dollar would even fall against Vietnam dong because of big supply. The central bank, in keeping the forex market stable and encouraging export, has had to buy a large amount of dollars from banks,” he said. </p>	<p>Ngan also rejected worries over the shortage of dollar funds in the coming time due to the country’s trade deficit – at US$4.6 billion in the first four months. He said that other foreign fund sources now could offset the trade deficit.</p>	<p>“Foreign direct investment disbursement in the first four months of the year was US$3.4 billion, while ODA capital amounted to US$1 billion, and incoming remittances totaled over US$2 billion. Those can well offset the trade deficit,” he ascertained.</p>	<p>He added that “if Vietnam dong is to depreciate against the U.S. dollar, the margin will be slim because the central bank can intervene in the market.” </p>	<p>The greenback on the unofficial market on Thursday afternoon traded at VND19,018 on buying and VND19,075 on selling, decreasing VND50 from the previous day. Meanwhile, the dollar price was quoted unchanged at banks, at VND18,099 on buying and VND19,050 on selling.</p></span>', 72, 375, 1, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(244, 'en', 'Sacomreal to list on southern bourse in July', 'HCMC – Sai Gon Thuong Tin Real Estate JS Company, or Sacomreal, signed agreements with three securities companies on Friday for consulting services to ready itself for listing on the southern bourse in July.', '', '2010-05-17', '<p>Dang Hong Anh, board chairman of Sacomreal, said at the signing ceremony that his company would seek to list 100 million shares on the Hochiminh Stock Exchange at the tentative reference price of VND50,000 a share. The agreements were signed between Sacomreal on one hand, and HCMC Securities, Thang Long Securities, and SBS on the other.</p><p>Sacomreal is currently the owner of 18 real estate projects in HCMC and some other provinces like Lam Dong, Hai Phong and Quang Nam. All its operational projects are in HCMC, including the Belleza project worth VND2.5 trillion, Hoa Binh project worth VND 100 billion, and an office building at 66 Pho Duc Chinh Street worth VND2 billion.</p><p>Sacomreal plans to start work on several new projects this year, including the Celadon City project covering 83 hectares worth US$1.6 billion, Phu Thuan project covering ten hectares with invested capital of nearly US$500 million, and Greenfield project worth US$141 million.</p><p>The property developer and trader targets revenues of VND1.87 trillion in 2010, with the real estate sector expected to generate VND1.78 trillion. It also target pre-tax profits at VND650 billion and a dividend of 30%.</p>', 72, 66, 1, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(245, 'en', 'Lending rates to fall gradually', 'HCMC – Given the stable macro economy, banks said that they would gradually decrease lending rates in Vietnam dong over the next couple of months with the central bank’s support.  ', '', '2010-05-18', '<p>After the Vietnam Banks Association called for banks’ cooperation to decrease both borrowing and lending rates two weeks ago, some banks have backed off from promotions and reduced deposit rates to about 11.5% per year. These measures will help cut lending rates in the future. </p><p>Pham Duy Hung, general director of Asia Vietnam Commercial Bank, said that his bank now gave loans to corporate customers at about 15% per year. </p><p>“But if the central bank continues to support State-owned banks to give loans at low rates of about 12-13% per year, joint-stock banks will also follow suit and could only ask for high lending rates from high-risk customers,” he said. </p><p>The general director of another joint-stock bank agreed with Hung, saying that if the central bank wants to pull lending rates down, they must inject cheap capital for banks via open market operations or lower reserve requirements to help reduce input costs. </p><p>Most banks now offer deposit rates at about 11.5-11.8% per year while lending rates are about 14.5-15.5% at joint-stock banks and 13.5-14.5% at State-owned banks. </p><p>However, the Government has asked the central bank to lower the lending rate to 12% per year and the deposit rate to 10% per year in the coming time. </p><p>Nguyen Tri Hieu, a board member of An Binh Commercial Bank (ABBank), said that the lending rate had reduced considerably compared to several months ago but to continue lowering rates, ABBank hoped the central bank would give it support. </p><p>“Interest rates cannot be decreased immediately. It takes time. With the desired lending rate of 12% per year, the inflation rate must be at 7% this year plus 2% for depositors and 3% for banks. That would be difficult to achieve at the moment,” Hieu said.</p><p>He said that this year inflation should be at about 10% to keep economic growth at 6.5%. </p><p>However, a 12% lending rate is possible this year if banks’ liquidity improves, he added. Commenting on the Government’s target to reduce the lending rate to 12% per year, Tran Hoang Ngan, member of the National Advisory Council for Monetary Policies, said that it could happen this year. </p><p>Banks have won many Government bond auctions recently so they have more access to cheap capital granted by the central bank via open market operations. </p><p>Furthermore, as lending terms on the open market operations are now longer, the target is feasible, Ngan said.</p><p>However, he added that it would require a reasonable amount of time to achieve.</p>', 71, 208, 1, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(246, 'en', 'January-April remittances via banks seen rising', 'HCMC – Commercial banks said inbound money remittances transferred via them in the first four months of the year were much better than last year as the global economy especially the U.S. has recovered. ', '', '2010-05-19', '<p>An executive of Vietcombank told the Daily that reports from branches of the bank nationwide showed that remittance revenue via the bank in the first four months amounted to US$434 million, increasing 14% year on year. </p><p>“That is a very positive result up to date as the bank this year targets only a 13% growth in remittance revenue,” the source said. </p><p>Meanwhile, Trinh Hoai Nam, deputy director of DongA Money Transfer Company under DongA Commercial Bank, said that remittances flowing into the country via the company had been strong this time and much better than the same period in 2009 when global economy was still reeling from the crisis. He said the company’s remittance revenue in the first four months of the year grew 20% from the same period last year. </p><p>At Sacombank, deputy general director Ho Xuan Nghiem said its remittance revenue in January-April was even better, totaling US$430 million, or a 33.5% increase year-on-year. </p><p>According to banks, given positive situation in the first four months of the year, they would achieve the remittance revenue target for the whole year. </p><p>The HCMC branch of the central bank reported that in the first quarter this year, remittance revenue transferred to the city was about US$964 million, increasing 18% from the same period last year. </p><p>Banks said amounts of dollars from remittances sold to the bank had been bigger as the dollar price at banks now was equal to the price on the unofficial market. </p><p>The U.S. dollar price on Tuesday was quoted by banks at VND18,980 on buying and VND19,020 on selling, falling VND30 from two days earlier. Meanwhile, the dollar on the unofficial market on Tuesday dropped VND20 also to VND18,990 on buying and VND19,010 on selling. </p><p>A broker on the unofficial market said forex trade had been slumped at this time given the narrower gap between unofficial and official dollar prices.</p>', 71, 342, 1, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(247, 'en', 'Demand for Vietnam dong bonds rise: HSC', 'HCMC – The demand for bonds in Vietnam dong has increased recently due to stable economic fundamentals, according to the latest report from the Hochiminh City Securities Corporation (HSC). ', '', '2010-05-20', '<p>The report referred to greater-than-expected results at recent bond tenders, citing an issuance of Government bonds on May 10 that mobilized as much as nearly VND4.53 trillion compared to the initial target of only VND2 trillion. </p><p>The mobilized fund is comprised of VND2.73 trillion worth of three-year bonds with an annual coupon of 11.25% and VND1.8 trillion worth of five-year bonds with 11.33% yield.The Government’s initial plan was to raise VND1 trillion for bonds of each term. </p><p>Most importantly, investors are interested in long-term bonds again given the successful underwritten issuance of five-year bonds. </p><p>Nguyen Tan Thang, economist and head of HSC’s Fixed Income Research Department, said that bonds in Vietnam dong were attractive to investors now as other investment channels such as gold and stocks were so volatile. </p><p>He added that banks’ liquidity had improved and inflation concerns had faded – factors that may have also added to investors’ interest in bonds.&nbsp;&nbsp; </p><p>According to HSC’s data, about VND17.2 trillion worth of Government bonds will be due this year, comprising VND3 trillion worth of bonds being matured in the second quarter and VND14.2 trillion matured in the second half of the year. </p><p>Therefore, the Government will issue bonds worth about VND18 trillion in the second quarter and a total VND100 trillion in 2010 to repay matured bonds and cover the State budget deficit, expected to be 6% of gross domestic product or equivalent to VND103 trillion, Thang said. </p><p>In the first four months of the year, only VND10.5 trillion worth of bonds were issued, so the pressure of issuing bonds to mobilize capital will increase for the rest of 2010. <br />	Thang said it would not be too difficult due to falling yield (meaning bond price increases) and fading inflation concerns. </p><p>Recently, foreign investors have participated more in the secondary bond market; accounting for 45% of the market’s traded volume. Thang said this proved that foreigners’ confidence in the local economy had improved. </p><p>“When buying bonds in Vietnam dong, important factors for foreigners are interest rate, inflation rate, and Forex rate. These are expected to stabilize in the future, making local bonds more attractive, especially to foreign investors,” Thang said.</p>', 72, 86, 1, 1, 'vietnam', NULL, NULL),
(248, 'en', 'HSBC arranges credit for steel firm', 'HCMC – HSBC Bank signed an agreement on Wednesday to arrange credits for Southern Hot Strip Steel Corporation (SHSSC) to build a hot strip steel mill in Vietnam with an annual capacity of two million tons.', 'upload/images/248.jpg', '2010-05-21', '<p>Under the deal, HSBC as the lead manager will represent four foreign-owned banks to loan SHSSC as much as US$369 million. </p><p>Duong Trung Toan, SHSSC general director, said that construction on the US$550 million factory in Ba Ria-Vung Ta Province would begin in the last quarter of this year.&nbsp; </p><p>“The steel plant will cover over 49 hectares in Phu My 1 Industrial Park and will take 18 months to build,” Toan added. Products manufactured at the factory will serve the local market. </p><p>Established in 2009 with chartered capital of US$158 million, SHSSC’s founding shareholders are Vietnam Steel Corporation with a 64% stake, Vietnam Rubber Group with 15%, Danang Steel Joint Stock Co. with 1% and Italy’s Danieli Group with 20%.</p><p>Anna Mareschi Danieli, area manager of financing and contracting for the Italian firm, said Danieli had signed an agreement with local enterprises on the establishment of this steel mill on the occasion of State President Nguyen Minh Triet’s official visit to Italy last December.</p>', 72, 404, 1, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(249, 'en', 'Foreign capital flows into Vietnam', 'HCMC – Foreign investors have participated in 32 consecutive net buying sessions since late March until this Tuesday, worth a total VND2.85 trillion, while their net buying value since early this year amounted to VND4.8 trillion – more than their entire net buying value in 2009. ', '', '2010-05-21', '<span class=\"Content\" id=\"ctl00_cphContent_lblContentHtml\">	<p>Foreigners’ favorite stocks were still large cap stocks, with good fundamentals such as HSG, SJS, BVH, and DIG. <br />		Phan Dung Khanh, deputy head of Kim Eng Securities Company’s Research Department, attributed aggressive foreign buying to the stable macro economic conditions, flexible monetary policies, and the good first-quarter results of many listed firms. 		<img align=\"right\" src=\"http://english.thesaigontimes.vn/App_Themes/Default/Imgs/SGTO_ADVERTISING.jpg\" alt=\"Vị trí đặt quảng cáo\" class=\"SGTOADV\" /></p>	<p>Meanwhile, Le Anh Thi, deputy general director of Au Viet Securities Company, told the Daily that the local stock market’s price per earning ratio (P/E) was about 10-11 times while some blue-chips even had P/E of 6-9 times – low compared to regional markets. As a result, the local stock market is attractive to foreigners, Thi said.</p>	<p>Foreigners are mostly long-term investors and mainly focus on valuation to choose stocks, much different to local investors’ strategies. </p>	<p>“At this time, Vietnam’s stock market still has good growth that can bring benefits to foreign investors,” Thi said. <br />		Le Van Thanh Long, SME Securities Company’s senior analyst, said, “Given basic indicators, Vietnam’s stock market is at an attractive level and contains few risks for long-term investors, contributing to foreigners’ continuous net buying status”. </p>	<p>However, Long said in the short term, foreign investors’ net buying status had little affect on the local market as most local investors were “wave surfers” while foreigners focused on long-term prospects.</p>	<p>“Monitoring the market, we can see that foreigners mainly buy stocks that had not sharply increased recently. Domestic investors usually miss out on those stocks,” Long said. </p>	<p>Given rising concern about the debt crisis in Europe, Johan Nyvene, CEO of Hochiminh City Securities Corporation, said that foreign foreigners were still net buyers, proving that the news had affected them little. <br />		“The impact of Europe’s crisis will hit the local stock market, but only slightly,” Nyvene said. </p>	<p>However, Long from SME Securities said that the crisis would affect foreign capital, especially as emerging markets like Vietnam are considered high risk. </p>	<p>Sharing Long’s view, Thi from Au Viet Securities Company, said that the debt crisis in Europe would affect Vietnam’s import and export market and foreign direct and indirect investment capital as foreign institutions had to restrict spending and narrow their investments, like in 2008. </p>	<p>“That would affect local investor sentiment,” Thi added. </p>	<p>The Vietnam Securities Depository Center granted trading codes in April to 141 foreign investors, including 26 institutions, according to Tuoi Tre. </p>	<p>In the first four months of the year, 437 foreign investors granted trading codes have invested in Vietnam’s stock market, increasing the total number of foreign trading codes to more than 14,000, including 1,267 institutional investors.</p></span>', 71, 262, 1, 1, 'vietnam', NULL, NULL),
(250, 'en', 'Bach Dang wins property deal', 'HANOI – The Malaysia-Vietnam joint venture Berjaya-Handico 12 on Thursday awarded a contract worth VND250 billion to local contractor Bach Dang Co. for developing a residential project named Canal Park Apartments in Hanoi.', '', '2010-05-14', '<span class=\"Content\" id=\"ctl00_cphContent_lblContentHtml\">	<p>Canal Park consists of two blocks of medium-rise apartments in a park environment alongside the canal. It is situated in Thach Ban Garden City that has a total investment of US$360 million. 		<img align=\"right\" src=\"http://english.thesaigontimes.vn/App_Themes/Default/Imgs/SGTO_ADVERTISING.jpg\" alt=\"Vị trí đặt quảng cáo\" class=\"SGTOADV\" /></p>	<p>Located 9km from central Hanoi, Thach Ban Garden City Township is a mixed development over a land area of 31.7 hectares.</p>	<p>The development site connects Thanh Tri Bridge with National Road No. 5 and new National Road No. 1 to the southeast. </p>	<p>Berjaya-Handico 12 is a joint between Malaysia’s Berjaya Leisure (Cayman) Ltd., a wholly owned subsidiary of Berjaya Land Bhd, and Hanoi Housing Investment and Development Joint Stock Co. No.12 on a 80:20 footing.</p>	<p>Speaking at the signing ceremony in Hanoi, Francis Ng, chief executive officer of Berjaya-Handico 12, noted the development of Canal Park, the first project of the whole Thach Ban Garden City, will help create favorable conditions for the developer to implement the US$360 million township project. </p>	<p>At the signing ceremony, Bach Dang Company also clinched a credit agreement with Eximbank’s Hai Phong City branch for loans to develop the Canal Park.</p></span>', 69, 99, 1, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(252, 'en', 'Colliers Int’l to market Vietnam’s tallest building', 'HCMC - Colliers International Vietnam late last week announced its appointment as exclusive marketing and leasing agent for the Keangnam Hanoi Landmark Tower, which once completed will be Vietnam’s tallest building.', 'upload/images/252.jpg', '2010-05-17', '<p>Keangnam Hanoi Landmark Tower is strategically located on Pham Hung Street, My Dinh. The project is positioned at the heart of the Cau Giay New Urban Area to the west of Hanoi’s city center. </p><p>This world class project developed by Keangnam Enterprise Ltd., a pioneer of the Korean construction industry with more than 60 years experience and success, has been designed with help from international architecture firms and will feature the prestigious five-star Intercontinental Hotel. </p><p>It is considered the most exciting development under construction in Hanoi on Monday with an innovative combination of beauty and grace. Upon completion, Keangnam Hanoi Landmark Tower will transform Pham Hung Street and the Cau Giay New Urban Area into a vibrant and dynamic central business district. </p><p>This architectural icon scheduled to open in the third quarter of next year will redefine Hanoi’s architectural landscape as the 17th highest skyscraper in the world. Previously, the total cost of the 336 meter high tower was estimated at US$1.05 billion.</p><p>The project covers over 4.6 hectares and the commercial tower will house 35 floors of Grade A office space. The offices will have a total gross area of approximately 154,770 square meters. </p><p>This development will comprise three towers including a luxurious department store, nearly 400 serviced apartments and 918 luxury apartments.</p><p>The development team’s expertise in building some of the world’s tallest skyscrapers is strengthened by the addition of ARUP as the structural engineers who were responsible for the structural engineering of Beijing Olympic Stadium. </p><p>Peter Dinning, general director of Colliers International Vietnam, said in a statement, “Like the Financial Tower in HCMC, Keangnam Landmark Tower marks the start of a new beginning for Hanoi. It is by any standard a success of aspiration, promise and collaboration. It will breathe life into the capital city and the completion of Keangnam Landmark Tower will finalize the transformation of Cau Giay as the new central business district of Hanoi.”</p><p>Colliers International Vietnam is also the exclusive marketing and leasing agent for the Financial Tower in HCMC, another skyscraper in the heart of the city that will be completed later this year.</p>', 69, 251, 1, 1, 'vietnam', NULL, NULL),
(253, 'en', 'CotecLand introduces Blue Sapphire Resort', 'HCMC – Cotec Real Estate Development and Investment Joint Stock Co. (CotecLand) has just introduced the Blue Sapphire Resort project in Vung Tau City with the total invested capital of VND1.5 trillion.', 'upload/images/253.jpg', '2010-05-19', '<p>Located four kilometers from the city center, the project will cover 77,000 square meters on the D5 Street next to Chi Linh Cua Lap beach. This will be a five-star resort with a 15-storey hotel, international convention center, restaurants, villas and bungalows, said CotecLand chairman Dao Duc Nghia.</p><p>The resort is designed by French architects of Archipel Joint Stock Co. while Savills and Swiss-Bell have been named the sole distributor and manager respectively, Nghia added. CotecLand has plans to begin the project next month for completion in 2015.</p><p>Under general planning of Ba Ria-Vung Tau Province until 2020, the resort will be next to the administrative, commercial and service center of the city.</p><p>The enterprise targets to invest VND300-500 billion in property and tourism projects in HCMC, Phan Thiet, Vung Tau cities, Binh Duong and Dong Nai provinces from now to 2020.</p><p>* In related news, the Cualo nine-hole golf course with a driving range and a club, the first phase of the Cualo golf resort project invested by three local companies, has just been inaugurated in Nghe An Province, becoming the first golf course there. </p><p>The 18-hole golf course is being built under the design and management of global leader IMG Worldwide USA. The 132.7 hectare resort in Nghi Huong Commune, Cua Lo Town is considered a key component of the province’s socio-economic development and will be invested with over VND1.5 trillion.</p><p>Tan Thanh Do Group (New City Group), Phu Tho Infrastructure Construction Investment Co. Ltd. and Minh Long Co. Ltd. are developing the Cualo golf resort project including an 18-golf course, two hotels and villas in the coastal town of Cua Lo. </p><p>A five-star hotel, coastal entertainment areas, a conference area, commercial area and additional luxury villas will also be developed.</p>', 69, 126, 1, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(254, 'en', 'HoREA says apartments for rent a potential segment', 'HCMC - The HCMC Real Estate Association (HoREA) is encouraging property developers to look into the segment of apartments for rent, foreseeing it as a potential segment but still open in the market given the increasing demand for accommodation.', '', '2010-05-20', '<p>Le Hoang Chau, chairman of HoREA, told the Daily on Wednesday that many property developers had overlooked the segment for years for the sake of profit. Instead, they have targeted commercial condo projects for quick investment return.</p><p>Chau said developing condos with apartments for rent was a must sector, for it would go into a niche in the market to satisfy accommodation demand of those who are unable to buy apartments whose values have gone beyond the reach of many homebuyers.</p><p>He compared Vietnam to other countries, saying people in other countries are used to living in leased houses and apartments, as not all can afford to buy property. However, many young Vietnamese families are not familiar with living on a leased property. They try to save money for years to buy a house or apartment of their own.</p><p>The fact is that costly land and housing prices, as compared to current monthly incomes, are a hindrance for many homebuyers, even when they can receive financial support from banks. Therefore, they have no way but leasing accommodation.</p><p>“We cannot tell people to live in leased apartments when there are no condo projects with apartments for rent,” Chau said, adding that property companies have not got involved in the segment, developing only small-sized apartments for rent.</p><p>Regarding small apartments, controversy exists as Dat Lanh Real Estate Co. petitioned a pilot project to build 20-square-meter apartments in HCMC’s District 12. Many say that with such an apartment, the developer should shift the properties to apartments for rent, not for commercial purposes.</p><p>Reality shows that some private families have developed small apartments for rent and have seen positive feedback from the market. </p><p>A small condo located on Tran Nao Street in HCMC’s District 2 is an example. The five-story building is developed on a piece of land for villas with 30 apartments as small as 25 square meters each. Besides security service, a camera system is installed to monitor the building day and night. </p><p>The building’s landlord says monthly rent is VND2.5 million, and most of her tenants are young families, white-collar workers and students. Currently there is no vacancy in the building.</p><p>“We encourage property companies, besides developing commercial condo projects, to study and join hands to develop condo projects with apartments for rent because of promised market demand,” Chau said.</p><p>The head of the city’s real estate association also said the Government should offer incentives attractive enough to lure property developers to the segment because condo projects with apartments for rent will contribute to settle down accommodation demand of people in the city.</p>', 69, 379, 1, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(255, 'en', 'RICS comes offering property training services', 'HCMC - The Royal Institution of Chartered Surveyors (RICS) says it will open a representative office in HCMC in the coming weeks to facilitate its first steps into the local property market by offering training courses for professional property services here in the country. ', '', '2010-05-21', '<p>Max Crofts, global president of RICS, told reporters at a news briefing held at the Intercontinental Hotel in downtown HCMC on Thursday that the London-based organization came to Vietnam not only to support its members working in the country, but also to help train Vietnamese staff to become qualified experts to serve the local property market in the years to come.	<img align=\"right\" src=\"http://english.thesaigontimes.vn/App_Themes/Default/Imgs/SGTO_ADVERTISING.jpg\" alt=\"Vị trí đặt quảng cáo\" class=\"SGTOADV\" /></p><p>Crofts said RICS would work with local organizations for training courses involving land, valuation and construction among others. Learners will have three years to cover different degree courses to become professional members of the organization.</p><p>He said professionalism will contribute to improving the transparency of the emerging property market in Vietnam.<br />	RICS said the global real estate industry is focusing its attention on new investment opportunities in Asian countries with signs of economic recovery.</p><p>According to analysts, the Asian property market is starting to pick up, especially in developing Southeast Asian countries where land is at a premium, offering investors great opportunities to participate in development projects with the potential for high returns.</p><p>“The current trends have ignited an interest in the property market in Vietnam, one of the world’s fastest growing countries with strengthening international links,” said Crofts, adding that property prices in Vietnam were rebounding as the global economic recovery continued.</p>', 69, 19, 1, 1, '', NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `tin` (`id`, `lang`, `tieuDe`, `tomTat`, `urlHinh`, `ngayDang`, `noiDung`, `idLT`, `xem`, `noiBat`, `anHien`, `tags`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(256, 'en', 'BCI Asia gives architecture awards', 'HCMC - BCI Asia, a leading construction information provider, announced Vietnam’s ten most-active architecture firms, as well as named the winners of its annual design contest FuturArc Prize 2010 in an award ceremony in HCMC on Friday.', '', '2010-05-24', '<p>The BCI Asia Top 10 Awards for 2010 were presented to Aedas Vietnam Ltd., Archipel JSC, Fosup Holdings Co., I.C.P. International Technical Construction Consultant Co., Ong &amp; Ong Co., RSP Architects Planners &amp; Engineers (Vietnam) Co., Sunjin Vietnam JVC, Transform Architecture Co., TT-As Architecture-Construction JSC and Vietnam National Construction Consultant Corp. </p><p>The portfolios of these architecture firms contain US$6 billion worth of properties scheduled to start construction in Vietnam this year, according to the organizer.</p><p>Matthias Krups, chairman of BCI Asia, said in a statement that the top ten architecture firms had turned the corporate objectives of clients into buildings that work for on Monday’s environment.</p><p>This is the 6th annual BCI Asia Top 10 Awards to celebrate the achievements of architecture firms in Hong Kong, Indonesia, Malaysia, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam.</p><p>BCI also named winners of its green building design competition called FuturArc Prize 2010, which is organized to seek new paradigms for designing a sustainable home. </p><p>In the professional category, Singaporean architects took home the first and second prizes and shared third prize with a competitor from Indonesia. Meanwhile, competitors from Hong Kong, Thailand and Australia dominated the top three prizes for the student category.</p><p>Last year, Vietnamese designers swept the two categories of the international design competition, winning both the professional and student design contests for green buildings.</p>', 69, 456, 1, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(257, 'en', 'Serviced and virtual office market expands', 'The serviced and virtual office market is gradually expanding due to the recent surge in office buildings located in HCMC’s center.', 'upload/images/257.jpg', '2010-05-24', '<p>Limited supply over the past few years made the business center viable for only a few professional companies. </p><p>However, lately the market has become competitive as more suppliers, including local providers, are offering increased office space for enterprises to establish their businesses. </p><p>In fact, one office provider plans to increase its space within the next year as it expects demand for serviced and virtual offices to increase dramatically in the future. </p><p>Compared to other countries, Vietnam’s serviced and virtual office market is relatively new and many companies are used to using conventional spaces to run their businesses. </p><p>However, according to services providers – whose primary customer base is foreign companies – more Vietnamese enterprises are establishing themselves in serviced and virtual offices.&nbsp; </p><p>The service is suitable for businesses with few staff, or starter companies that require a professional workplace. </p><p>Normally, service providers rent an entire floor, or two, in office buildings located in the central business district, which is then fitted with all the necessary facilities.&nbsp; </p><p>Prices range depending on the chosen package.</p><p>Many small companies are opting to rent serviced and virtual office space to save money, and to be within the city center. </p><p>Tran Lan Phuong, assistant office manager of GoodPack Limited Vietnam’s representative office, which is located on the seventh level of Me Linh Point Tower on Ngo Duc Ke Street in downtown HCMC, said last week that, “We have chosen a serviced office to save costs and to boost our company’s professional image”. </p><p>Phuong said that her company, including three staff members, moved to the building a year ago from a house in HCMC’s District 3. </p><p>She said the company paid about US$1,200 per month to rent the space – much less compared to when they operated in the house, as they had to pay electricity, internet, telephone and security bills there, as well.</p><p>William Willems, serviced and virtual office provider Regus Group’s regional vice president for South East Asia, Australia and New Zealand, said that companies could save up to 60% on their monthly costs by using the service. </p><p>Regus Group has operated in Vietnam for over 10 years and provides office space spanning some 5,000 square meters in both HCMC and Hanoi. </p><p>It has 300 tenants who have set up their businesses in three office buildings including the Press Club in Hanoi and HCMC’s Saigon Tower and Me Linh Point. </p><p>Willems says Regus will double its office space in the next 12 months, with three additional locations in other cities besides Hanoi and HCMC, given Vietnam’s positive economic growth. </p><p>HCMC now has 10 office buildings including Me Linh Point Tower on Ngo Duc Ke Street, Saigon Tower on Le Duan Boulevard, Saigon Trade Center on Ton Duc Thang Street, Centec Tower on Nguyen Thi Minh Khai and Kumho Asiana Plaza on Hai Ba Trung Street. </p><p>Recently, the group conducted its bi-annual Regus Business Tracker Survey, polling 15,000 respondents in 75 countries, including Vietnam, about their companies’ financial performance and expectations for growth. </p><p>The survey showed that Vietnam has weathered the global crisis better than many other countries, and that the net growth of the nation’s companies was positive at&nbsp; more than 44%. </p><p>In addition, the survey found that many respondents believe full momentum for economic recovery will occur in 2010’s first half. </p><p>Willems said that the country’s large population, young workforce and positive economic growth encouraged foreign companies to expand their businesses to Vietnam, including Regus Group. </p><p>He predicted that a shift from traditional commercial property leasing to solutions that accommodate flexible working systems will occur and would likely play a large part in the economic recovery. </p><p>Due to increased supply, serviced and virtual office providers will compete strongly, offering more space for tenants in the near future. </p>', 69, 226, 1, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(258, 'en', 'SSG Group launches first phase luxury residence', 'HCMC – SSG Group Joint Stock Co late last week announced to have wrapped up the first phase of its property project named Saigon Pearl located along Nguyen Huu Canh Street in HCMC’s Binh Thanh District after five years of construction.', 'upload/images/258.jpg', '2010-05-25', '<p>This is a residential complex covering a 10-hectare site stretching along the Saigon River and designed with a villa section including 126 units, eight 37-story apartment buildings, a complex for office building, hotel and commercial center and other facilities.</p><p>Dinh Ngoc Ninh, general director of SSG Group, said the group had invested some US$750 million to develop Saigon Pearl, whose first phase includes two blocks of buildings, Ruby and Topaz, with some 1,000 apartments from 84 to 140 square meters each. There are penthouses and duplex apartments designed on the four top floors of the buildings.</p><p>Ninh said the group would finish the Sapphire building in October this year, providing the market 526 new luxury apartments and offering more options for homebuyers in the city. As planned, 50% of the Sapphire’s apartments will be launched into the market by June.</p><p>He said the second phase of the project would be continued with other important serviced facilities. As scheduled, the developer will put into service the Saigon Pearl International School in August and launch a section for retail podium, banking service and postal and communication services. In another project it plans to invest VND350 billion to develop a primary school and a bilingual high school which will receive students by autumn next year.</p><p>Ninh said the group would spend some VND400 billion building a yacht club and a marina that will stretch 500 meters along the Saigon River. When in place, the marina will accommodate 130 canoes and yachts, and those services are expected to offer business opportunities for the company as it can sell leisure and entertainment services on the river.</p><p>Construction for next year will include a complex of office building, hotel and commercial center which requires an investment of US$300 million.</p><p>Established in 2003, SSG Group has 18 member companies active in real estate investment, education development and mine ores.</p>', 69, 272, 1, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(272, 'en', 'Travel firms aim high for golf tours', 'HCMC – Golf is not popular in Vietnam but tour operators believe the sport has the ability to lure both international and local travelers. As a result, many tour organizers have been promoting golf tours in recent years.', '', '2010-05-13', '<p>Asian Trails Co. Ltd arranged a familiarization trip for two editors from a Switzerland-based golf magazine two months ago, to play golf at five courses in the country.</p><p>The magazine promoted golf in Vietnam after its staff explored the country’s many courses themselves. </p><p>Bui Viet Thuy Tien, managing director of Asian Trails, said, “We don’t have many golf travelers but we want to develop the potential segment. Along with promoting golf tours via specific magazines, we will use other marketing channels to promote the sport in the country”. </p><p>At Saigontourist Travel Services Co., golf tourists had increased in the last two years, especially domestic golfers. In addition, more local people were buying outbound and domestic golf tours. Before that, the tours were only popular among foreign golfers who purchased them via the internet and others who bought MICE (meetings, incentives, conventions, and exhibitions) tours including golf activities. </p><p>Doan Thi Thanh Tra, marketing manager of Saigontourist, said, “We are arranging outbound tours for around two groups per month while more domestic tours have sold after the Lunar New Year holiday. For domestic tours, golfers like to go to Phan Thiet, Dalat, Danang and Tam Dao.”&nbsp;&nbsp; </p><p>The company on Wednesday launched a regular outbound tour to Burei every Sunday for domestic golfers.</p><p>Hanoi-based Ocean Travel Company has a website with information about the country’s golfing scene, including news, promotions, and accommodation for tourists at <a href=\"http://www.vietnamgolfplay.com/\">www.vietnamgolfplay.com</a>. </p><p>Pham Van Minh, the company’s director of sales, said that as golf is relatively new in Vietnam, the country is only receiving limited numbers of tourists in the segment. Many are businessmen from Europe, Singapore and Malaysia.</p><p>“We’ve decided to run the website because we believe the segment has potential. We are preparing for an increase in travelers,” he said.</p><p>Other companies have also launched websites dedicated to golf tours. Even Golfasian Co. Ltd in Bangkok, Thailand has set up a website about Vietnam’s golf tours at <a href=\"http://www.vietnamgolfvacation.com/\">www.vietnamgolfvacation.com</a>. </p><p>However, some tour operators said international golfers complain that golf fees in Vietnam are higher than in other countries like Thailand, causing some to travel to cheaper destinations instead.&nbsp; </p><p>“But, many golf courses are putting in new services. We hope the fees will lower when new competitors join the market and the golf courses will launch promotions to attract golfers,” Tien of Asian Trail said.</p>', 74, 261, 1, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(273, 'en', 'Vietravel promotes Vietnam in China', 'HCMC - Vietravel Marketing and Tourist Company, or Vietravel, will work with China’s Travel Channel China from May 16 to 21 to film a documentary in HCMC, Nha Trang and Hanoi. ', 'upload/images/273.jpg', '2010-05-15', '<span class=\"Content\" id=\"ctl00_cphContent_lblContentHtml\">	<p>The group will visit distinguished and beautiful architectures in HCMC such as the Central Post Office, the Opera House, Ben Thanh Market, Cho Lon Town and Goddess Thien Hau Pagoda, discover food and beverage styles of the Saigonese and learn about Vietnamese-style foot massage. 		<img align=\"right\" src=\"http://english.thesaigontimes.vn/App_Themes/Default/Imgs/SGTO_ADVERTISING.jpg\" alt=\"Vị trí đặt quảng cáo\" class=\"SGTOADV\" /></p>	<p>The crew will go to Nha Trang, a place recognized as one of the 29 most beautiful bays of the world by the Club of the Most Beautiful Bays of the World. </p>	<p>In Nha Trang, the group will visit Hon Mun, Hon Tam and Tri Nguyen Aquarium, discover beautiful beaches via scuba diving services at Vinadive Center of Vietravel and visit Thap Ba Ponagar and Long Son Pagoda and bathe in the mud. </p>	<p>In Hanoi, the crew will film scenic spots such as Ba Dinh Square, One Pillar Pagoda, Hoan Kiem Lake and Ngoc Son Temple and go around the city to explore its 36 ancient streets and watch traditional water puppetry.</p>	<p>Travel Channel China is a leading channel for travel information throughout China. It broadcasts 24 hours in 31 provinces and attracts over 300 million viewers.</p></span>', 74, 45, 1, 1, 'vietnam', NULL, NULL),
(274, 'en', 'City’s tourism dept surveys tourists', 'HCMC – HCMC’s Department of Culture, Sports and Tourism will conduct a survey among the city’s top tourism source markets namely the U.S., Taiwan, Singapore, Malaysia, Australia and South Korea as well as another for Japan, a tourism official said. ', '', '2010-05-15', '<span class=\"Content\" id=\"ctl00_cphContent_lblContentHtml\">	<p>Nguyen Viet Anh, head of the department’s Travel Division, told the Daily that the survey’s purpose was to give the division an insight into what travelers expect when visiting the city. 		<img align=\"right\" src=\"http://english.thesaigontimes.vn/App_Themes/Default/Imgs/SGTO_ADVERTISING.jpg\" alt=\"Vị trí đặt quảng cáo\" class=\"SGTOADV\" /></p>	<p>To obtain the information, the division will distribute questionnaires to tourists and collect data concerning market trends and visitors’ demands from various other sources. </p>	<p>“Results from the survey will help us to identify specific needs and develop tourism products and promotion programs for each market in the coming time,” he said.</p>	<p>Anh said the division expects to complete the survey next month.</p>	<p>Apart from the Vietnam National Administration of Tourism’s (VNAT) market research, few surveys have been conducted to gauge HCMC’s tourism sector in recent years, even though it receives more international visitors than any other region in the country. </p>	<p>Anh said that the department is collaborating with the HCMC University of Economics to carry out a large-scale survey on District 1’s Pham Ngu Lao backpacker quarter surrounded by De Tham, Bui Vien, Pham Ngu Lao and Do Quang Dau streets. </p>	<p>“The city has planned to spend VND500 million on the survey. Both the city government and the tourism sector expect to find helpful information to develop the quarter,” Anh said.</p>	<p>The survey will be completed late this year. </p>	<p>According to the department, HCMC has already received about 1.08 million international travelers in the first four months of this year, up 9% year-on-year, or more than half of the country’s total foreign visitors.</p>	<p>The tourism industry has contributed around VND12.6 trillion to HCMC this year, an annual increase of 19%.</p></span>', 74, 445, 0, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(275, 'en', 'Russian travel firms survey tourism facilities in Binh Thuan', 'HCMC- Representatives of 14 Russian travel companies on Sunday finished a familiarization trip to survey tourism facilities in the resort city of Phan Thiet in Binh Thuan province, a local source said.', '', '2010-05-17', '<p>Nguyen Van Khoa, chairman of the Binh Thuan Tourism Association, said the trip started on May 12 and that the representatives had explored the quality of the accommodations and tourist sites in Ham Tien-Mui Ne. </p><p>The association cooperated with a local travel company to organize the familiarization trip. The representatives are visiting other attractions in the country.</p><p>According to Khoa, Russians account for 30% of international travelers to the province and often have long stays at seaside resorts in Phan Thiet.</p><p>The Binh Thuan Province Department of Culture, Sports and Tourism reports the province welcomed nearly 220,000 tourists last month, bringing the total for the first four months of this year to 832,000, up 13.4% year-year. Nearly 130,000 of these are foreigners.</p><p>Tourism revenue reached nearly VND750 billion, up over 34%.</p>', 74, 88, 0, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(276, 'en', 'Saigontourist opens golf tours to Brunei Darussalam', 'Saigontourist has just organized a new summer tour called Playing Golf in Brunei Darussalam for three or four days with prices from US$628. ', '', '2010-05-18', '<p>Just 15 minutes from Brunei Airport, Royal Brunei Golf and Country Club’s 18 holes play a total of 6,172 meters. This golf course was built in a tropical forest and has welcomed many members. </p><p>Visitors will also challenge their skills at the Empire Golf Course which plays 6,425 meters. This course belongs to the six-star seaside Empire Hotel and Resort and hosts international competitions. </p><p>Saigontourist has lately organized golf tours to Thailand, China and the U.S. as a high class service which attracts many tourists. The company organizes similar tours to Dalat, Phan Thiet and Danang where there are many golf courses. Saigontourist also has a four-day tour called Brunei-Kota Kinabalu for US$649 that departs from HCMC on June 13 and 27.</p>', 74, 108, 0, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(277, 'en', 'VNAT to probe outbound travel firms over tour quality', 'HCMC – The Vietnam National Administration of Tourism (VNAT) will launch inspections into travel firms that operate outbound tours to Thailand, Cambodia and China following complaints over tour quality, an official said.', '', '2010-05-18', '<span class=\"Content\" id=\"ctl00_cphContent_lblContentHtml\">	<p>Vu The Binh, head of the Travel Department under VNAT, told the Daily that the department would begin the inspections next month. </p>	<p>Inspectors will focus primarily on HCMC-based travel companies that have been arranging tours to Cambodia, and other firms located in the Central region that organize overland trips to Thailand. </p>	<p>He said that the department had sent documents explaining the inspections to the provincial Departments of Culture, Sports and Tourism in relevant localities. </p>	<p>“We’ve decided to monitor travel companies that arrange tours to these three countries because we have received complaints about low quality, unsafe tours and unfair competition among some companies in these markets,” Binh said.</p>	<p>He said the department would fine companies that did not measure up, or even revoke their licenses, in a bid to protect local tourists.&nbsp; </p>	<p>At a recent tourism meeting in HCMC, Binh said that Vietnam has more than 800 travel companies with licenses to organize inbound and outbound tours. About 600 companies operate outbound tours. </p>	<p>The tourism department had found it difficult to oversee travel companies’ operations as many failed to send required reports to them. </p>	<p>He said that, according to the Tourism Law, companies who do not hand in their reports on time would be issued warning for once from the department before their licenses are revoked.&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>	<p>“We will tighten activities to monitor the sector’s operation to close down bad companies,” he said.</p>	<p>VNAT issued a document this March asking tour operators to stop taking local tourists to casinos in foreign countries and to protect travelers abroad. The tourism agency has also asked local firms to stop sending tourists to unsafe destinations.</p>	<p>The warning was issued as some companies were arranging outbound tours with low quality services for local travelers. Some tourists have even had accidents while abroad.&nbsp; </p>	<p>In the document, the tourism agency also asked local culture, sports and tourism departments to monitor travel companies’ outbound tour activities.</p></span>', 74, 276, 0, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(278, 'en', 'Demand for U.S. tours increases', 'HCMC – More Vietnamese are buying outbound tours to the U.S., especially for the summer, according to local tour operators. ', '', '2010-05-18', '<p>Some travel companies in HCMC namely Perfect Tour, Carnival Tour, Saigontourist and Viettours said that travel to the U.S. had increased more than other long-haul destinations like Europe and Australia. Some companies have reported 15-20% growth in the segment this season.</p><p>The tour operators said that travel to the U.S. was cheaper than visiting Europe, for example. In addition, it is now easier for Vietnamese travelers to obtain visas to travel to the U.S.&nbsp; </p><p>Nguyen The Khai from Perfect Tour Travel Co Ltd said that the company’s tours to America in the next month have sold out with 200 tourists. Around 150 people have booked tours for this July. </p><p>“Normally, the situation remains good in August. Our tourists to the U.S will increase 15% this summer. It’s good business,” he told the Daily.</p><p>Tourists have increased about 20% at Carnival Tour. The company will have around 50 to 100 tourists per month, while Viettours said their growth was 15%.</p><p>Saigontourist Travel Service Co., has yet to calculate the total number of travelers but Lam Tu Khoi, deputy manager of the company’s Outbound Department, said that local tourists to the U.S. are increasing yearly. The company is carrying out more activities to develop the market. </p><p>Luu Dinh Phuc, director of Viettours, said that traveling to the U.S. is increasing along with the length of tourists’ stays – increasing the market’s revenue.&nbsp; </p><p>“Many Vietnamese tourists have chosen eight-day tours in the past but now many people are interested in two-week or 17- or 18-day tours,” he said.</p><p>In U.S. dollars, tour prices are the same or slightly higher than last summer. However, local travelers will pay more because of the high U.S. dollar to Vietnam dong exchange rate. </p><p>“Around 50% of total local tourists to the U.S. are for travel only. The remainder combines travel with visiting relatives, followed by people who come to travel and explore universities and colleges. The last group is expanding,” Khoi said. </p><p>Khai from Perfect Tour had a similar view. He said that the company has 200 tourists traveling to the U.S. next month. Of them, twenty families, each with three to four members will combine travel with exploring education options. The company only had four to five families last June.</p><p>Local tour operators will promote U.S. tours to many potential customers.&nbsp; </p><p>Dinh Kim Phuong, director of Carnival Tour, said that, “Tourists can buy a U.S tour for over US$2,000. Instead of visiting three to four regional destinations, customers can travel to one long-haul destination. We will expand our customer base for better business”.</p>', 74, 56, 0, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(279, 'en', 'Unclear stats about Vietnam’s tourism sector', 'HCMC – Vietnam’s tourism sector does not have a clear database system to gauge international visitors to the country, making it difficult for travel firms to develop business plans and define appropriate products for various markets.  ', '', '2010-05-19', '<p>The Vietnam National Administration of Tourism (VNAT) quoted a report from the General Statistics Office last month, that said about 16,000 foreign visitors had visited the country by sea in the January-April period, down 36.4% year-on-year – very different compared to travel companies’ statistics. </p><p>Saigontourist Travel Service Co., Viet Excursions, and OSC Travel (SMI) Co., Ltd. primarily receive cruise ships in Vietnam. </p><p>Saigontourist said the company alone had 25,000 international cruise passengers in the first four months of this year, the same as last year’s period. </p><p>Viet Excursions said it welcomed thousands of travelers this February, as did OSC Travel.</p><p>Vietnam’s tourism sector frequently sees differing sea traveler figures. </p><p>An official from VNAT’s Travel Department said that the tourism sector receives&nbsp;information about market sources, travel purposes and the number of visitors from the General Statistics Office.&nbsp;</p><p>The industry plans to create market development and promotion programs based on the figures. </p><p>“We will review the real situation to send feedback to the General Statistics Office because they are carrying out the job,” he said.</p><p>He added that the tourism sector is unable to provide specific statistics as many travel companies fail to send their business reports. </p><p>“Travel companies should send their reports to the administrating office every six months but many do not, making it difficult for us to compile statistics,” he said.</p><p>A database that includes information about tourist spending, average length that visitors stay, and total travelers in Vietnam is essential for both the tourism department and the industry. </p><p>However, both sides have complained that a clear database system including all relevant information does not exist. </p><p>La Quoc Khanh, deputy director of HCMC’s Department of Culture, Sports and Tourism, complained about a VNAT report concerning international tourists in the city at a meeting this March. The report said that HCMC had few visitors. </p><p>Ngo Minh Duc, director of HG Travel, the general sales agent for American Airlines in Vietnam, said the tourism sector does not provide enough figures for entrepreneurs to assess the market and determine trends to develop products and set prices. </p><p>“We receive true figures from American Airlines that help us to know when we can increase prices or when we need to go down. This information helped up to overcome the challenges in 2009,” he said at the aforementioned meeting. </p><p>Nguyen Van My, director of Lua Viet Picnic Company, said that Cambodia still has fewer tourists than Vietnam; however, the country monitors the industry well. </p><p>The Cambodian tourism sector sends an analysis report to industry members every six months – something that Vietnam still fails to do.</p>', 74, 454, 0, 1, 'vietnam', NULL, NULL),
(280, 'en', 'City traders asked to register for grand sale program', 'HCMC – The HCMC Department of Culture, Sports and Tourism is inviting traders to join the Impressive Vietnam Grand Sale 2010 program and will receive registrations from next month, a tourism official said.', '', '2010-05-20', '<p>La Quoc Khanh, deputy director of the department, told the Daily on Wednesday that shopping centers, retail outlets and other traders could register at the department office at 140 Nguyen Dinh Chieu Street in District 3. </p><p>“Such traders can register with the department on their promotions without limit on the discount percentage,” he said.</p><p>The program is part of a national marketing campaign called Vietnam – Your Destination initiated by the Vietnam National Administration of Tourism (VNAT). Under the program, the departments of Culture, Sports and Tourism and Industry and Trade of HCMC, Danang and Hanoi will organize the program in August and September to offer discounts of 10%- 40% for both local and foreign customers.</p><p>Khanh said the promotion program in August would attract around 63 shopping centers and restaurants that have been recognized under the city’s Standard Tourism Service. </p><p>he forthcoming program will be an additional promotion event alongside the yearly promotion program of the Department of Industry and Trade.</p><p>“The city’s tourism sector has a Standard Tourism Service system as well as the yearly program of the Department of Industry and Trade, so the city’s grand sale program will be a bit different compared to those in Danang and Hanoi,” Khanh said.</p><p>Vu The Binh, head of the Travel Department under VNAT, said relevant departments of Hanoi and Danang were in the process to carry out the program.</p><p>“They’re receiving registrations from traders. We are following up the process in the three cities and will make an official announcement of the Impressive Vietnam Grand Sale 2010 to customers as soon as possible,” he said.</p><p>Binh told the Daily that along with the promotion program, the three cities planned to organize promotion fairs as well. HCMC plans to hold its fair in November while Hanoi and Danang’s will take place in December.</p>', 74, 100, 0, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(281, 'en', 'Summer tours attract tourists', 'Domestic travel companies have reported earlier-than-ever bookings for this summer’s tours. Vietravel said their summer tours for May were full while Fiditour was full for the tours departing in June. ', '', '2010-05-21', '<p>Nguyen Thi Tuyet Mai, PR director of Fiditour, told the Daily, “Last year, travelers booked tours for their summer vacation ten days before departing, but this summer they have registered two weeks and more before departing. Therefore, we have received more than 3,000 guests for half of the month.” 	<img align=\"right\" src=\"http://english.thesaigontimes.vn/App_Themes/Default/Imgs/SGTO_ADVERTISING.jpg\" alt=\"Vị trí đặt quảng cáo\" class=\"SGTOADV\" /></p><p>Explaining the reason for the early registrations, Le Hong Viet Thao from Vietravel said, “Tour programs of this year are various and tour operators have opened more new tours. Moreover, travel agencies offer more promotions to customers in order to stimulate tourism such as discounts or gifts from a lucky draw. So, we attract tourists sooner.” </p><p>Domestic destinations attracting the most attention are beaches such as Nha Trang, Phan Thiet, Phu Quoc or highlands such as Dalat, Ba Na and Sapa. Nguyen Chung Thuy, manager of the PR Department of Lua Viet Tours, said “tourists choose these destinations due to hot weather and the habit of Vietnamese travelers.” </p><p>Domestic travel agencies increase the numbers of tours and tourists that they will serve such as Vietravel will organize a tour for 70,000 customers and Fiditour 35,000 for 400 summer tours.</p><p>Foreign destinations that draw many tourists are China, Hong Kong, Malaysia, Korea, the U.S. and European countries. Saigontourist is an example, attracting more than 2,000 tourists for their high standard tours Premium Travel going to these places.</p>', 74, 139, 0, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(282, 'en', 'Organizing board of Miss World Vietnam dismissed', 'Khanh Hoa Province has decided to establish a new organizing board for the 2010 Miss World Vietnam which will be hosted at Vinpearl Land in Nha Trang City from May 20 to August 30.', '', '2010-05-14', '<span class=\"Content\" id=\"ctl00_cphContent_lblContentHtml\">	<p>The old organizing board, including 15 members led by the vice chairman of the Khanh Hoa Province People’s Committee, Le Xuan Than, will be dismissed. The new organizing board will be assembled by Vinpearl Land. The change will not affect the pageant’s process. The new board will carry out the pageant under the direct instruction of the steering board of the contest at the national level, including representatives of the Ministry of Culture, Sports and Tourism, the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, the Central Committee of the Ho Chi Minh Communist Youth Union, Vietnam Television and Khanh Hoa Province. The proposal of Vinpearl Land is waiting for approval from the Ministry of Culture, Sports and Tourism.</p>	<p>The winner will be awarded a prize worth VND500 million, the biggest award ever in a domestic pageant.</p></span>', 74, 397, 0, 1, 'vietnam', NULL, NULL),
(283, 'en', 'Binh Thuan lures new tourist projects', 'The Department of Culture, Sports and Tourism of Binh Thuan Province has announced the province has approved ten tourist projects to be developed in Phan Thiet City. The province has 430 tourist projects with registered investment of VND61 trillion to cover over eight hectares. ', 'upload/images/283.jpg', '2010-05-15', '<span class=\"Content\" id=\"ctl00_cphContent_lblContentHtml\">	<p>To attract investors, the province is upgrading infrastructure, promoting destinations to local and foreign tourists, diversifying services and building up tourist products and promotions.		<img align=\"right\" src=\"http://english.thesaigontimes.vn/App_Themes/Default/Imgs/SGTO_ADVERTISING.jpg\" alt=\"Vị trí đặt quảng cáo\" class=\"SGTOADV\" /></p>	<p>Binh Thuan Province attracts millions of local and foreign tourists every year. The province’s Phan Thiet is well-known for its stunning beaches, nice sand dunes and historical and cultural relics.</p>	<p>*Binh Thuan Province has licensed Anh Dao Co. Ltd. to develop Takalau Residences Club and Resort in Phu Hai Ward, Phan Thiet City.</p>	<p>The project will cover 10,800 square meters at a cost of VND55 billion. The resort will feature deluxe bungalows, entertainment areas, spas, gyms and sports to meet the demands of local and foreign tourists.</p>	<p>The project is expected to be completed in 2012.</p></span>', 74, 70, 0, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(284, 'en', 'Japanese T’rung Association debuts', 'The Consulate General of Japan in Vietnam held a ceremony on Sunday to debut the Japanese T’rung Association, aiming to advertise Vietnam’s unique culture and arts to the “Land of the Rising Sun,” reports Vietnam+.', '', '2010-05-18', '<p>Vietnamese Ambassador to Japan Nguyen Phu Binh showed his delight at the establishment of the association and said he hoped it would help promote cultural exchange between the countries. The chairman of the new association said the purpose was to bridge the two cultures.</p><p>The association’s vice chairwoman, musician Kumiko Okuri who performs the T’rung instrument, expressed her thanks to the Vietnamese teachers who had taught her to play and to the Vietnamese Embassy for setting up the association.</p><p>She also reported on the association’s upcoming performances, one a concert to celebrate the Thang Long-Hanoi millennial anniversary.</p><p>At the ceremony, musicians from the bands Tre Viet and Trio and Okuri performed together, receiving a warm reception and high appreciation from the audience.</p>', 74, 157, 0, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(285, 'en', 'Japanese T’rung Association debuts', 'The Consulate General of Japan in Vietnam held a ceremony on Sunday to debut the Japanese T’rung Association, aiming to advertise Vietnam’s unique culture and arts to the “Land of the Rising Sun,” reports Vietnam+.', '', '2010-05-18', '<p>Vietnamese Ambassador to Japan Nguyen Phu Binh showed his delight at the establishment of the association and said he hoped it would help promote cultural exchange between the countries. The chairman of the new association said the purpose was to bridge the two cultures.</p><p>The association’s vice chairwoman, musician Kumiko Okuri who performs the T’rung instrument, expressed her thanks to the Vietnamese teachers who had taught her to play and to the Vietnamese Embassy for setting up the association.</p><p>She also reported on the association’s upcoming performances, one a concert to celebrate the Thang Long-Hanoi millennial anniversary.</p><p>At the ceremony, musicians from the bands Tre Viet and Trio and Okuri performed together, receiving a warm reception and high appreciation from the audience.</p>', 74, 75, 1, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(286, 'en', 'Phap Hoa Supermarket opens in town', 'Phap Hoa Supermarket opened at Pho Quang Pagoda, 64/3 Pho Quang Street, Ward 2 in HCMC’s Tan Binh District last week.', '', '2010-05-18', '<p>This is the first Buddhist supermarket in Vietnam, specializing in worship offerings, Buddhist monk and nun’s clothes, Buddhist prayer books, Buddhist publications, recordings on tapes and disks, vegetarian food, fresh flowers and office supplies for everyone. </p><p>The supermarket which is under the management of the Buddhism Association of HCMC covers 1,000 square meters at the pagoda. It will spend a part of its profits doing charity activities.</p><p>Mani Media Co. Ltd. was also opened at the pagoda, supplying Buddhist cartoons, stories and lectures as well as shooting Buddhist events.</p><p>*The Lieu Quan Buddhist Cultural Center and the Buddhism Center in Thua Thien-Hue Province opened the Week of Buddhist Culture 2010 on Sunday in the ancient capital of Hue. </p><p>Many local authorities, monks, Buddhists and tourists attended the celebrations in the lead up to the millennial anniversary of Thang Long-Hanoi, reports Vietnam+.</p><p>During the week, which also celebrates Buddha’s 2554 birthday, a range of events will take place, including an antiques exhibition featuring more than 100 historic pieces from Tran Dinh Son’s collection, dating from the pre-Thang Long (Dai Lai) Ly, Tran and Le dynasties. </p><p>Scholars such as Cao Huy Thuan, Tran Dinh Son, Thai Kim Lai and Ho Tan Phan will deliver speeches about Thang Long’s royal citadel and Buddhism in Vietnam. </p><p>The organizers will also hold music shows and vegetarian food will be available at Nguyen Dinh Chieu Street. There will also be a Buddha’s throne show on Huong River.&nbsp; <br />	The event will run until May 22.</p>', 74, 407, 1, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(287, 'en', 'Festival features the peoples of ASEAN', 'The Ministry of Information and Communications has launched a festival of photos, documentaries and TV reports that feature the land and peoples of ASEAN member countries, reports Vietnam+.', '', '2010-05-19', '<p>Deputy Minister of Information and Communications Do Quy Doan said the idea was proposed by Vietnam at the 10th Conference of the ASEAN Ministers Responsible for Information.</p><p>The festival is dedicated to promoting the images of the lands, peoples and development of all member countries of ASEAN, thus enhancing solidarity and mutual understanding and bolstering cooperation to build the ASEAN Community and implementing the ASEAN Charter. The festival also aims at celebrating Vietnam’s ASEAN chairmanship in 2010 and 15 years of its accession to the bloc.</p><p>The festival is open to organizations, authors and individuals who hold citizenship of an ASEAN country. Submitted work must not have been in any international contest.<br />	Prizes will be presented on the occasion of the 17th ASEAN Summit scheduled to take place in Hanoi in October.</p>', 74, 309, 0, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(288, 'en', 'Le Fruit Triathlon 2010 comes to Mui Ne', 'Le Fruit Triathlon 2010, a long-standing multi-sport event, will take place in Phan Thiet City, Binh Thuan Province on May 29. Le Fruit Triathlon, which was created in 2002 by a French national living in Vietnam, is named after the natural juices made from fresh fruits ethically sourced in Vietnam. This is the ninth time Viet Adventure has organized the sports event.', '', '2010-05-20', '<p>The departure of Le Fruit Triathlon 2010 will be on Suoi Nuoc Beach in Mui Ne, a well-known tourist destination in Binh Thuan Province, combining sea swimming in the fairly lively East Sea, mountain biking crossing famous sand dunes, and trail running on the wet, steep and narrow white beach. The run is a scenic out and back, mostly flat along the beautiful tropical beach.</p><p>With the ninth edition of Le Fruit Triathlon, Viet Adventure is creating a family sport event, focusing on children. </p><p>Following the race there will be a post-race meal and refreshments provided at the awards ceremony. Trophies will be awarded to winners. In addition, there will be a raffle drawing with many gifts, such as airplane tickets and luxury resort vouchers.</p><p>The organizer will be visiting the school of the fishermen village Suoi Nuoc next to Mui Ne to offer bicycles and pay for the scholar fees of orphans and single-parent children.</p><p>*A group of representatives of 14 travel agents from Novosibirsk City in Russia last week came to Phan Thiet and made a survey on local resorts and hotels to promote the image of Phan Thiet as well as local hospitality services to Russian tourists for the tourist season 2010-2011.</p><p>“The group is really satisfied with tourist services, splendid landscapes, historical and cultural relics as well as courteous serving manner of the staff in resorts, hotels, restaurants as well as tourists areas in Phan Thiet,” said Mariya Votchel of S7 Tour Company. She also added that 90% of Russian tourists to Vietnam visited Mui Ne in Phan Thiet City.</p><p>The authorities and heads of resorts, hotels and tourist agents are preparing promotions for tourists this summer season.</p><p>The survey of the group is one of the activities of the Farm Trip program organized by Nhat Minh International Travel Company from May 9 to 23.</p>', 74, 325, 0, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(289, 'en', 'Kien An Cung Pagoda', 'A sea view seen from Dai Lanh Lighhouse - Photo: Kieu GiangIf on a tour to Sa Dec Town,  don’t forget to pass by Kien An Cung Pagoda of Huynh Thuy Le’s family, which is related to the French novel “L’amant” (“The Lover”) by Marguerite Duras ', 'upload/images/289.jpg', '2010-05-20', '<p>Located in Ward 2, Sa Dec Town, Dong Thap Province, the one thousand square meter Kien An Cung Pagoda was built between 1924 and 1927 by Huynh Thuan, Huynh Thuy Le’s father, and a group of Chinese people from Phuc Kien Province living in Sa Dec Town at that time. </p><p>Kien An Cung Pagoda worships Ong Quach Thanh Vuong Cong (Quach Aristocrat), whose hometown was Fujian Province. Quach Aristocrat helped Tong Thai To (King Song) mount punitive expeditions against a smaller nation Nam Duong (Southern Tang), one of the ten kingdoms in south-central China created following the Tang Dynasty from 937-975, and establish the Song Dynasty. </p><p>The pagoda, whose front faces the Cai Son River, was built as the shape of the Chinese word meaning merit&nbsp; including three compartments of which the largest was used for the shrine. The roof was made meticulously with three layers, first tiles, second bricks and third more tiles. Most of the material used for building the pagoda was brought from Fujian Province. </p><p>Every year, the pagoda celebrates rituals on February 22 and August 22 of the lunar calendar. And every three years, Kien An Cung Pagoda sets up altars to celebrate requiems for the dead souls and pray for the peace of the country. </p><p>Inside the pagoda is an altar to worship Huynh Thuy Le and his wife. In April, 1990, Kien An Cung Pagoda was recognized as a national cultural and historical relic by the Ministry of Culture, Sports and Tourism. </p><p>If you want to take a trip to Sa Dec Town, 140 kilometers from HCMC, and visit places related to Huynh Thuy Le, a famous good landlord living there, or listen to his love story and life, you can book a one day tour at Dong Thap Tourist JSC at 178 Nguyen Hue Street, Ward 2, Cao Lanh City, Dong Thap Province, by calling 067 3855 638 or 067 3852 139, or by emailing <a href=\"mailto:dothatour@dongthaptourist.com\">dothatour@dongthaptourist.com</a>.</p>', 74, 199, 0, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(290, 'en', 'Ho Ngoc Thuy – the man of pearls', 'Phu Quoc Island is endowed with many natural advantages and is well-known as a home to precious shining pearls. For about ten years, the island has been known as the country’s largest pearl farm and the most famous brand of pearl transplanting is Ngoc Hien of the owner named Ho Phi Thuy. ', 'upload/images/290.jpg', '2010-05-21', '<p>Life of Thuy must be a beautiful story about a strong will overcoming the fate of poverty and hardship. At 19, after graduation from high school, he left his poor homeland in Ha Tinh for Phu Quoc and started the job of diving to find natural pearls. Thuy lived with a group of fellow farmers on a small island about five kilometers from Phu Quoc Town and separated from the bustling outside life.</p><p>“At first, I was not used to diving 20 meters so my ears bled and my rib-cage seemed to break out. One of my divers died and another got paralyzed caused by brain artery breakout while diving. I was so scared but I could not give up my way for my earnings,” said Thuy. After three years of working hard and living thriftily, Thuy became a diver at a depth of 60 meters to find pearls and could buy a small boat.</p><p>In 1990, Thuy was hired by a Japanese pearl transplanting company on Phu Quoc after they had bought many natural pearls from him. They also bought his boat and paid him VND1.7 million a month, a pretty good salary at that time.</p><p>Since then, Thuy spent half of each day diving and the rest following Japanese expert Horikiri Seiji to learn pearl transplanting. Thuy shared, “Natural pearls are often evaluated higher than manmade ones but natural shapes are often husky while manmade pearls are brighter and smoother. To have beautiful manmade pearls, artisans are required a high experience and talented skills, especially they have to know the proper time for pearls to grow in the best conditions.”</p><p>“Naturally, when the pearls open their mouths, they will release a special protective substance which will become pearls. Therefore, the artisans have to know how to stimulate the pearls to open their mouths to carry out transplantation and the kernels must be put carefully in the middle of the pearl meat,” he added.</p><p>Thuy applied all his knowledge and passion from the Japanese expert and finally started making beautiful pearls by himself. “Thuy embraces a strong will and a profound passion for the job, so his products are as good as products of Japanese experts,” said Seiji.</p><p>In 1997, the company closed during the global economic recession. Thuy bought all the company’s machines and stocked pearls for VND400 million. Then, he established Ngoc Hien Pearl Transplanting Company, the first company of it kind in Vietnam at that time. He also invited Seiji to stay and develop the company. To promote his products to tourists, Thuy opens a show room on a beach in Duong To District. He also owns a 20-hectare pearl farm on the shore for tourists to visit and learn how to transplant and grow pearls.</p><p>After twenty years of living and making pearls, Thuy is well-known as one of the country’s leading experts in transplanting pearls. He has finished procedures to buy a 100%-foreign-invested pearl transplanting company in Vung Tau and he is going to expand his operation in Cambodia.</p><p>With a blazing passion to make attractive pearls, Thuy deserves to be called the man of pearl.</p>', 74, 20, 0, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(291, 'en', 'Hanoi’s old quarter is uneasy to decide what needs upgrading', 'Vietnam until now has not found proper methods to restore Hanoi as the local authorities have not identified what are eligible to be restored in the old quarter. The case has even been researched and discussed by more than 20 countries, said Dao Ngoc Nghiem, former head of Hanoi City’s Planning and Architecture Department, at the international forum Sharing Experience on Restoring Old Cities: Genova and Hanoi in Hanoi on Friday.', '', '2010-05-24', '<p>The old quarter has 112 historical and cultural relics and hundreds of old houses with typical architectures, of which the most striking is the house located at 38 Hang Dao Street built in the seventeenth century in the Le Dynasty by the Dong Lac family. The house keeps many stele boards dating back to 1856. The house located at 87 Ma May is also famous for its elegant architecture and Oriental decorations.</p><p>The restoration and preservation of old street areas are making local authorities uneasy as old street areas have downgraded through ups and downs of historical epochs and need urgent renovation. However, the city now is stuck in different initiatives of experts from Australia, Japan, France and Switzerland. For example, the project of Australia in 1995 that proposed to adjust the entire old quarter had not been realized. Last year, the University of Civil Engineering in Hanoi collaborated with Japanese experts to map out ways and means to preserve and develop the old quarter by upgrading an old street area or making an underground living space for old houses to increase settlement area. But this way cannot be applied as the underground story will affect the solidity and structure of houses.</p><p>Currently, Hanoi has about 1,100 houses worthy of renovations and repairs. In old quarter areas there are about 20% new houses, 63% downgraded houses, 12% heavily damaged houses and 5% houses that do not meet living conditions. The difficulty is houses are close together or next to relics, causing bad effects on architecture and structures of relics when renovation is carried out.</p><p>Nghiem said the most practical thing was keeping the streets clean and clear and assuring living conditions for locals. Some of them are difficult to decide to leave their living places as their lives are associated with their traditions, ancestors, neighbors and business.</p><p>Therefore, the project of resorting old streets is sluggish as residents are hard to move.</p><p>Nghiem added that projects need clear policies and exact selections for what needs to be restored and upgraded.</p>', 74, 5, 0, 1, '', NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `tin` (`id`, `lang`, `tieuDe`, `tomTat`, `urlHinh`, `ngayDang`, `noiDung`, `idLT`, `xem`, `noiBat`, `anHien`, `tags`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(316, 'en', 'A woman who loves antiques', 'Nguyen Thi Tu Anh, or Bach Diep, has an antique collection of more than 1,000 artifacts made of stone, terracotta or bronze. Anh’s antiques date back from hundreds to thousands of years. ', 'upload/images/316.jpg', '2010-01-15', '<span class=\"Content\" id=\"ctl00_cphContent_lblContentHtml\">	<p>Most of her antiques are from the North of Vietnam, such as her thousand year old stone dog set and her set of terracotta works from the Dong Son 		<img align=\"right\" src=\"http://english.thesaigontimes.vn/App_Themes/Default/Imgs/SGTO_ADVERTISING.jpg\" alt=\"Vị trí đặt quảng cáo\" class=\"SGTOADV\" />period of 2,500 years ago.</p>	<p>“When I was a child, I had a deep passion for antiques when I saw a lot of religious antiques in my grandmother’s house,” said Anh.</p>	<p>The passion grew day by day. In 1986, Anh moved to HCMC and worked as a tour guide, giving her chances to return home in the North. “At that time, I often took tourists to visit pagodas and whenever I saw people throwing out antiques, I bought them for my house,” she added.</p>	<p>In the 1990’s, Anh started buying old objects at cheap prices.</p>	<p>“I love to learn history and antiques are witnesses of history. When you hold an antique of an era, you can know a part of the educational level and customs of that epoch. Therefore, I buy antiques to preserve the cultural soul of the country as well as to appreciate the past,” Anh said.</p>	<p>Enthusiasts offer high prices for her collections but Anh refuses.</p>	<p>Collectors without sufficient knowledge to distinguish real antiques from fakes are easily swindled.</p>	<p>To prevent fraud, Anh and other collectors established an antique club for antique lovers to introduce their collections and exchange experience and knowledge.</p>	<p>Anh also writes articles about antiques. “I want to hand down the passion to antique lovers.”</p>	<p>Anh returns to the North twice a month to hunt for antiques. She hopes to open a private museum to preserve the culture of the nation and introduce young generations to ancient culture and history.</p></span>', 52, 48, 1, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(318, 'en', 'Poet Huu Loan dies at age 95', 'Huu Loan, author of the famous poem “Mau Tim Hoa Sim” (Violet Color of Sim Flowers), passed away at his home in Thanh Hoa Province on March 18 at the age of 95, reports Tuoi Tre. ', 'upload/images/318.jpg', '2010-03-22', '<p>Loan was born in Van Hoan Hamlet, Nga Linh Commune, Nga Son District, Thanh Hoa Province in 1916, receiving his high-school diploma in 1943. He worked as a teacher before joining the Viet Minh. He was the vice chair of the uprising committee in Nga Son District during the August Revolution. Before 1945, he was a freelance writer for the Van hoc (Literature) newspaper.</p><p>	<img align=\"right\" src=\"http://english.thesaigontimes.vn/App_Themes/Default/Imgs/SGTO_ADVERTISING.jpg\" alt=\"Vị trí đặt quảng cáo\" class=\"SGTOADV\" />After 1945, he was appointed as a member of the Thanh Hoa Province administration, in charge of culture, <br />	education, trade and administration.</p><p>During the French war, he joined the People’s Army, serving in Battalion 304. After 1954, he worked at the <br />	Van nghe (Literature and Arts) newspaper and after retirement, returned to his hometown.</p><p>Loan is known for a poem titled “Deo Ca” and especially “Mau Tim Hoa Sim,” the latter written in 1949 after his first wife died. Tan Binh Electronics Company bought the copyright for this poem for VND100 million in 2004.</p><p>The poet suffered severe rheumatism in the last two years of his life. His funeral rituals took place on March 19.</p>', 52, 492, 1, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(319, 'en', 'Launch of 2010 Businessmen Club’s new managing board', 'The 2030 Businessmen Club under the Saigon Times Club celebrated its eighth anniversary on March 27, 2010. The club’s new managing board from 2010 to 2012 was instated on the occasion. ', 'upload/images/319.jpg', '2010-03-31', '<p>The new managing board – who will represent the club’s fifth term – consists of nine male members, mostly born in the 1980s. </p><p>Nguyen Thanh Phong, born in 1981 and manager of Ngac Nhien Service Trading and Construction Co., Ltd was voted the 2030 Businessmen Club’s new chairman. </p><p>During this office term, the club will abolish previous age limitations (from 20 to 39). The club will be open to all enterprises’ managers and senior executives at any age. </p><p>Tran Dinh Vinh, deputy editor-in-chief of the Saigon Times Group and chairman of the Saigon Times Club, said the club’s predominantly young membership would signal a new generation.</p><p>“After eight years of operation with many highlighted activities attached to young businessmen under 40, the new managing board is considered as a transition from the 1960s and 1970s generations to the 1980s generation who, it is hoped will demonstrate creativity and connectivity,” he said. </p><p>To mark this special occasion, the managing board has admitted 15 new members, raising the club’s total membership to 250 people.</p>', 52, 318, 1, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(320, 'en', 'Denmark supports Yersin University in tourism training', 'Yersin University in Dalat City inaugurated a hotel-restaurant vocational training center on Tuesday under a project called Danisa sponsored by the Danish government to improve global competitiveness and to answer the demand for human resources in the tourism sector in Dalat City, Lam Dong Province. ', 'upload/images/320.jpg', '2010-04-01', '<p>The inauguration was attended by Peter Lyshoslt Hansen, Danish ambassador in Vietnam, the managing board of Yersin University, authorities of Lam Dong Province and leaders of the tourism sectors of neighborin	<img align=\"right\" src=\"http://english.thesaigontimes.vn/App_Themes/Default/Imgs/SGTO_ADVERTISING.jpg\" alt=\"Vị trí đặt quảng cáo\" class=\"SGTOADV\" />g provinces.</p><p>“Vietnam is a country with plentiful human resources which need to be trained methodically to contribute to sustainable economic development. That’s the reason Danisa sponsors this center,” said Hansen.</p><p>The center will train skills in reception, room service, waiting tables, bartending, cooking and English.</p><p>High school graduates nationwide may apply to study at the center. After finishing the course, students will get a certificate and be reimbursed the entire school fee by local government.</p><p>This project lasts until June.</p>', 52, 114, 1, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(328, 'en', ' STF provides computers for remote schools', 'A project to provide computers for schools in remote areas co-organized by the Saigon Times Foundation (STF) and Thoi bao Vi tinh Sai Gon, a publication specilizing in information technology under the Saigon Times Group, has been carried out. ', 'upload/images/328.jpg', '2010-05-09', '<table width=\"100%\">	<tbody>		<tr>			<td><span class=\"Content\" id=\"ctl00_cphContent_lblContentHtml\">					<p>The project was born after surveys made by the foundation on trips to donate scholarships to students who suffered from typhoons Ketsana and Mirinae in the Central and Central Highlands last November. Many schools in remote areas in the provinces of Quang Nam, Quang Ngai, Kon Tum and Phu Yen have no computer, which has been known as a luxury item, and students have no access to approach and study information technology.</p>					<p>CSC Vietnam is the pionner in response to the project having donated 20 computers to Nong Son District in Quang Nam Province. These computers arrived at the People’s Committee of Nong Son District on Monday. </p>					<p>“The education department of Nong Son District will provide ten computers to Son Vien Elementary School, five computers to Que Trung Elementary School and Que Ninh Elementary School five computers,” said Pham Phu Thuy, vice chairman of the People’s Committee of Nong Son District. </p>					<p>Apart from CSC Vietnam, PepsiCo Vietnam, Fulbright Economics Teaching Program and Victoria Can Tho Hotel have committed to donate computers to schools in remote areas of Quang Nam Province and Can Tho City among others. </p>					<p>For further information about the project, contact Ms. Ngoc Xuan, deputy director of the Saigon Times Foundation, at 3740 2712 or 0918 346 919 or email ngocxuan@thesaigontimes.vn.</p></span>                                    				<script type=\"text/javascript\">				//<![CDATA[				var text=document.getElementById(\"ctl00_cphContent_lblContentHtml\").style.fontSize;					                    var Zoom=(text.replace(\"px\",\"\")==8)?12:text.replace(\"px\",\"\");					                    function TextZoom(Step)					                    {						                    if(Zoom>30 || Zoom<8)							                    Zoom=12;						                    Zoom=Zoom+Step;						                    document.getElementById(\"ctl00_cphContent_lblContentHtml\").style.fontSize=Zoom+\"px\";					                    }				//]]>				</script>                                </td>                            		</tr>                            		<tr>                                			<td align=\"right\" style=\"color: Blue; font-family: Tahoma; font-size: 12px; padding-right: 20px;\">                                                                    <br />				</td>		</tr>	</tbody></table>', 54, 146, 1, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(329, 'en', ' STF provides computers for remote schools', 'A project to provide computers for schools in remote areas co-organized by the Saigon Times Foundation (STF) and Thoi bao Vi tinh Sai Gon, a publication specilizing in information technology under the Saigon Times Group, has been carried out. ', 'upload/images/329.jpg', '2010-05-09', '<p>The project was born after surveys made by the foundation on trips to donate scholarships to students who suffered from typhoons Ketsana and Mirinae in the Central and Central Highlands last November. Many schools in remote areas in the provinces of Quang Nam, Quang Ngai, Kon Tum and Phu Yen have no computer, which has been known as a luxury item, and students have no access to approach and study information technology.</p><p>CSC Vietnam is the pionner in response to the project having donated 20 computers to Nong Son District in Quang Nam Province. These computers arrived at the People’s Committee of Nong Son District on Monday. </p><p>“The education department of Nong Son District will provide ten computers to Son Vien Elementary School, five computers to Que Trung Elementary School and Que Ninh Elementary School five computers,” said Pham Phu Thuy, vice chairman of the People’s Committee of Nong Son District. </p><p>Apart from CSC Vietnam, PepsiCo Vietnam, Fulbright Economics Teaching Program and Victoria Can Tho Hotel have committed to donate computers to schools in remote areas of Quang Nam Province and Can Tho City among others. </p><p>For further information about the project, contact Ms. Ngoc Xuan, deputy director of the Saigon Times Foundation, at 3740 2712 or 0918 346 919 or email ngocxuan@thesaigontimes.vn.</p>', 54, 76, 1, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(330, 'en', 'Phuong Nam Corp. to open five new bookstores this year', 'Phuong Nam Cultural Corporation will inaugurate five new bookstores this year for a total of 35 nationwide, Phan Ngoc Diem Han, marketing manager of the company, told the Daily on the sidelines of the re-opening of its bookstore in HCMC’s Go Vap District on Saturday. ', 'upload/images/330.jpg', '2010-05-17', '<p>The five new bookstores will be located in HCMC, Hanoi, Hue and Dalat. Of the five, the Phuong Nam Cultural Center in Hue will open on June 1. This center will be a book caf&eacute; model and a place for distinguished handicraft products of Hue’s trading villages on over two thousand square meters. </p><p>“This center will be opened to welcome the 2010 Hue Festival on June 6 and is the first model that Phuong Nam Corp. inaugurates,” added Han. Together with its current 30 bookstores, including eight book caf&eacute; centers, Phuong Nam will extend its business in Dalat by opening the first bookstore on Hoa Binh walking street on August 15.&nbsp; </p><p>Phuong Nam’s revenue from bookstores last year was VND650 billion, “but we only expect this year’s turnover increase at 15% year-on-year due to the economic recession,” Han said. </p><p>Founded in 1982, Phuong Nam Cultural Corp. specializes in publishing books and selling stationery. The company recently cooperated with foreign partners Envoy Media, Longman, Indochina Capital, Caravelle Fund and East Media Holdings Inc. to extend its business scope to the high-class cinemas of Megastar Cineplex, exclusively producing movies and music discs.</p>', 54, 371, 1, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(331, 'en', 'Berjaya Corp. and STF build classrooms in Nong Son District', 'The Saigon Times Foundation (STF) and Berjaya Vietnam have installed three classrooms, a restroom and a well at Phuoc Ninh Elementary School in Phuoc Ninh Commune, in the mountainous Nong Son District in Quang Nam Province. ', 'upload/images/331.jpg', '2010-05-18', '<p>The construction is worth VND563 million with VND500 million donated by Berjaya Corporation Berhad (Malaysia) from the proceeds of the 2009 Berjaya-Saigon Times Golf Tournament. The three classrooms cover 170 square meters, the restroom 20 square meters and the well is 15 meters deep. </p><p>“On behalf of the local people and students, we want to show our gratitude to all the benefactors who have supported facilities to the school. With these new classrooms we can reduce the student number in each class to improve education and training quality.</p><p>From now on, 245 students from the first to the fifth grade will no longer be in an overload situation due to lack of classrooms,” said Pham Phu Thuy, vice chairman of the People’s Committee of Nong Son District.</p>', 54, 96, 1, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(332, 'en', 'Time to put helmets on children', 'Asia Injury Prevention Foundation (AIP Foundation) is launching a new two-day campaign targeting parents’ education and awareness on child helmet use in support of the enforcement of Decree 34 and child helmet use. ', 'upload/images/332.jpg', '2010-05-20', '<p>A mobile education unit is visiting 20 primary schools during lunch and after-school pick up times in HCMC and Hanoi to distribute leaflets, speak with parents and answer any questions about the decree and child helmet use. </p><p>These activities took place on Wednesday and continue on Thursday when Decree 34 comes into effect. From Thursday, adults carrying children aged six or older without a helmet or the helmet improperly buckled on their motorbike will be fined VND100,000-200,000. </p><p>As part of the campaign, AIP Foundation plans to identify areas throughout the country with low child helmet use and will use this focused intervention to educate parents.</p><p>Staff of AIP Foundation have sent a letter to the parents of all primary students in HCMC and Hanoi involved in the foundation’s programs to request them to pledge a proper helmet on their children’s head before they get on a motorbike.</p><p>“Parents vaccinate their children against tuberculosis, polio and measles. Putting a helmet on your child reduces their chance of serious brain injury by 79% and of death by 42%,” said Mirjam Sidik, executive director of AIP Foundation.</p><p>“Helmets are like a vaccine, they protect your child’s health,” Sidik said in a statement AIP released on Wednesday.</p><p>Founded in Vietnam in 1999, AIP implements school-based and nationwide public awareness education programs focused on road safety in Vietnam, Thailand and Cambodia. </p><p>In November, AIP together with the FIA Foundation and the World Bank Global Road Safety Facility launched the Global Helmet Vaccine Initiative with the mission of putting a helmet on every head in the Decade of Action for Road Safety.</p>', 54, 60, 1, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(379, 'vi', 'Cụ già thoát chết thần kỳ khi rơi từ tầng 10', 'Một cụ ông Trung Quốc được giải cứu sau khi rơi xuống từ căn hộ tầng 10 thuộc khu chung cư ở Bắc Kinh trong khi đang lau cửa sổ.', '', '2011-06-14', '								<script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"/Library/Common/Player/swfobject.js\"></script>											<div id=\"poly_video\" style=\"text-align:center;width:100%;\">													<span id=\"FlashPlayer51347\" class=\"Normal\" align=\"center\">B&#7841;n c&#7847;n c&#224;i <a href=\"http://www.macromedia.com/go/getflashplayer\">Flash Player</a> &#273;&#7875; xem &#273;&#432;&#7907;c Clip n&#224;y.</span>				<script type=\"text/javascript\">				var sFlashPlayer51347= new SWFObject(\"/Library/Common/AdsPlayer/player.swf\",\"playlist\",\"480\",\"380\",\"7\");				sFlashPlayer51347.addParam(\"allowscriptaccess\",\"always\");				sFlashPlayer51347.addParam(\"allowfullscreen\",\"true\");				sFlashPlayer51347.addParam(\"wmode\",\"transparent\");				sFlashPlayer51347.addVariable(\"displayheight\",\"380\");				sFlashPlayer51347.addVariable(\"width\",\"480\");				sFlashPlayer51347.addVariable(\"height\",\"380\");				sFlashPlayer51347.addVariable(\"backcolor\",\"#000000\");				sFlashPlayer51347.addVariable(\"frontcolor\",\"#000000\");				sFlashPlayer51347.addVariable(\"lightcolor\",\"#000000\");				sFlashPlayer51347.addVariable(\"shuffle\",\"false\");				sFlashPlayer51347.addVariable(\"repeat\",\"list\");				sFlashPlayer51347.addVariable(\"extjs\",\"Poly_ShowAdsVideoLarge\");				sFlashPlayer51347.addVariable(\"skin\",\"/Library/Common/AdsPlayer/classic/classic.xml\");				sFlashPlayer51347.addVariable(\"file\",\"/Service/FlashVideo/Playlist2.asp?Id=51347\");				sFlashPlayer51347.addParam(\"flashvars\",\"skin=/Library/Common/AdsPlayer/classic/classic.xml&extjs=Poly_ShowAdsVideoLarge&shuffle=false&amp;repeat=list&amp;volume=60&amp;smoothing=true&amp;screencolor=000000&amp;lightcolor=000000&amp;frontcolor=000000&amp;start=0&amp;provider=http&amp;playlistfile=/Service/FlashVideo/Playlist2.asp?Id=51347&amp;autostart=false\");				sFlashPlayer51347.write(\"FlashPlayer51347\");			</script>			</div>			<p class=Normal>Theo <em>Telegraph</em>, đội cứu hộ được gọi tới sau khi những người hàng xóm hốt hoảng nhìn thấy người đàn ông nằm ngược vắt vẻo bên ngoài khung sắt cửa sổ tầng 8 của họ.</p><p class=Normal>Lính cứu hộ nhanh chóng trấn an cụ ông và buộc dây thừng vào đôi chân đang buông thõng xuống, trong khi ông cụ vẫn bám chặt hay tay vào các khung sắt.</p><p class=Normal>Phải mất một lúc thợ giải cứu mới thuyết phục được ông cụ buông tay ra để họ có thể đưa ông xuống đất an toàn.</p><p class=Normal>Người đàn ông này đã được đưa vào bệnh viện điều trị và điều lạ kỳ là ông chỉ bị một vài vết xây xát nhỏ.</p><p class=Normal align=right><strong>Anh Minh</strong></p>', 9, 40, 0, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(391, 'vi', 'Không bao giờ bỏ cuộc', 'Khi người ta mất tất cả cũng là lúc người ta cần phải mạnh mẽ hơn bao giờ hết. Vì thất bại và mất mát của ngày hôm nay không là gì cả so với những gì bạn sẽ gặp phải trong tương lai.', '', '2011-06-14', '				<p class=Normal><font>Mình sinh ra và lớn lên ở nơi quê hương Miền Trung nắng lửa mưa dầu. Gia đình mình nghèo nên tụi mình thiếu thốn đủ mọi thứ. Giống như bao nhiêu bạn bè cùng trang lứa sau khi học xong PTTH tụi mình khăn gói vào Sài Gòn để học đại học. </font></p><p class=Normal><font>Đối với tụi mình giảng đường đại học luôn có sức lôi cuốn thật lạ thường. Để rồi bao đêm thức trắng ôn thi kết quả là mình đậu vào Đại học Bách khoa TP HCM. Mình rất vui và hạnh phúc. Ngày tựu trường nhìn các bạn sinh viên ai cũng thật đẹp, gương mặt ai cũng rạng ngời. Riêng mình niền vui ấy không được trọn vẹn. Vì trước mắt mình vấn đề cơm áo gạo tiền làm cho mình không thể không trăn trở. Ngày tháng rồi cũng trôi qua thật nhanh.</font></p><p class=Normal><font>Giấc mơ giảng đường đại học đã không trọn vẹn. Mẹ mình bị tai nạn giao thông nằm liệt giường 3 năm là từng ấy thời gian mình gác lại giấc mơ đại học. Đi làm với bao thử thách và cám dỗ mình đã không còn nhớ đến lời hẹn ước một ngày trở lại học tiếp. Thời gian bảo lưu đã hết mình thể tiếp tục học được nữa. Đó cũng là thời gian mẹ mình mất, tất cả với mình thế là hết. </font></p><p class=Normal><font>Tình cờ mình đọc trong một quyển sách cũ có câu: \"Khi người ta mất tất cả cũng là lúc người ta cần phải mạnh mẽ hơn bao giờ hết. Vì thất bại và mất mát của ngày hôm nay không là gì cả so với những gì bạn sẽ gặp phải trong tương lai. Cuộc đời luôn có những phần thưởng lớn cho những ai không nản lòng và biết hy vọng\". Mình đã đứng dậy và làm lại từ đầu. </font></p><p class=Normal><font>Thất bại và thành công luôn theo mình. Đối với mình 5 lần thất bại đổi lấy một lần thành công. Mình luôn có niềm tin vào bản thân và công việc.</font></p><p class=Normal><font>Hiện tại mình đang điều hành công ty nhỏ kinh doanh bên lĩnh vực CNTT. Tuy còn nhiều khó khăn và thử thách phía trước nhưng mình tin công ty mình sẽ phát triển tốt và hướng tới là niêm yết trên sàn chứng khoán. Mình mong các bạn hãy vững niềm tin. </font></p><p class=Normal><font><strong>Lương Bình Nguyên </strong></font></p>', 12, 69, 0, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(392, 'vi', 'Sapa vào mùa cấy', 'Vào mùa này tận dụng những cơn mưa rừng đổ đấy nước trên những thửa ruộng bậc thang đồng bào các dân tộc H\'Mông, Dao đỏ, Tày tiến hành cấy lúa. Đây cũng là mùa đẹp nhất để đi du lịch Sapa.', 'upload/images/2011-06-14 10-26-16--mua-gat.jpg', '2011-06-14', '				<font></font><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=3 width=\"100%\" align=center border=0><tr><td><img src=\"hinh/2011-06-14 10-26-16--mua-gat.jpg\" width=500 height=335 border=1 /></td></tr><tr><td>Mùa cấy hay còn gọi là mùa con nước đổ, diễn ra vào trung tuần tháng 6 hàng năm</td></tr><tr><td><img src=\"http://vnexpress.net/Files/Subject/3b/a2/b0/5f/mua-cay-1.jpg\" width=500 height=323 border=1 /></td></tr><tr><td>Những thửa ruộng bậc thang được cày mới và đổ đầy nước dưới ánh nắng mặt trời như những tấm gương khổng lồ phản chiếu ánh sáng lấp lánh.</td></tr><tr><td><img src=\"http://vnexpress.net/Files/Subject/3b/a2/b0/5f/mua-cay-2.jpg\" width=500 height=335 border=1 /></td></tr><tr><td><img src=\"http://vnexpress.net/Files/Subject/3b/a2/b0/5f/mua-cay-3.jpg\" width=500 height=312 border=1 /></td></tr><tr><td>Đây làm mùa vụ rất quan trọng của đồng bào các dân tộc thiểu số của huyện Sapa thuộc tỉnh Lào Cai.</td></tr></table><p class=Normal><strong><font face=Arial size=2>Diêm Đăng Dũng</font></strong></p>', 3, 195, 0, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(402, 'vi', 'Mỗi giọt máu cho đi, một cuộc đời ở lại', '(Dân trí) - “Mỗi giọt máu cho đi, một cuộc đời ở lại”, hàng ngàn học sinh, sinh viên, công nhân viên chức, lực lượng vũ trang, công nhân... đã chia sẻ những “giọt hồng” quý giá để cứu những người bệnh hiểm nghèo.', 'upload/images/2011-06-14 10-29-48--hienmaunhandao1_9f798.JPG', '2011-06-14', '<div align=center><img style=\"MARGIN: 5px\" align=center src=\"hinh/2011-06-14 10-29-48--hienmaunhandao1_9f798.JPG\" width=450 _fl=\"\"></div><div align=center><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma; FONT-SIZE: 10pt\">SV Đại học Vinh tham gia hiến máu tình nguyện.</span></div><div align=center>&nbsp;</div><div>“Những năm học phổ thông, một lần vào bệnh viện thăm bố bạn thân. Bác ấy bị tai nạn giao thông, mất máu nhiều, phải chuyền máu. Hồi đó, nguồn máu khan hiếm, suốt cả buổi sáng chờ đợi vẫn không mua được máu để chuyền. Nhìn cảnh bố nằm chờ máu, bạn và mẹ bạn khóc than, em không kìm nổi lòng mình. Nhưng, em không đủ can đảm để hiến máu cứu bố của bạn...”, đó là lời tâm sự em Nguyễn Văn Sơn, sinh viên Trường ĐH Vinh. </div><p>Chỉ đến khi, Sơn bước chân vào giảng đường Đại học, được trường, được khoa, được các anh chị vận động tuyên truyền, được tiếp cận với các kiến thức cho máu -nhận máu, em mới hiểu ra rằng, hiến máu đúng cách không gây hại đến sức khỏe, hiến máu cứu người là nghĩa cử cao đẹp. </p><p>Sau đó Sơn viết đơn, tình nguyện xin hiến máu. Một lần, hai lần và trong 3 năm học tại trường, Sơn đã tình nguyện hiến máu 7 lần. Sơn vinh dự được Bộ Y tế tặng Bằng khen, UBND tỉnh tặng Bằng khen và được vinh danh từ lễ “Giọt Xuân hồng” năm 2010. Nhưng với Sơn, không bằng khen, phần thưởng nào có thể sánh được với niềm hạnh phúc của người bệnh, và không gì tự hào bằng khi nghĩ đến những giọt máu của mình đã cứu được mạng sống của nhiều người.</p><div>Với em Nguyễn Thị Quỳnh Trang - Trường Đại học SPKT Vinh phải “trốn” cả nhà để đi hiến máu tình nguyện. Bố mẹ Trang là công nhân xây dựng, khi nghe con xin phép đi hiến máu, dường như “sốc” rồi răn đe có, dọa nạt có và cả giận con gái, chỉ mong làm sao không để con “dại dột” cho máu. </div><div align=center>&nbsp;</div><div align=center><img style=\"MARGIN: 5px\" align=center src=\"http://dantri4.vcmedia.vn/7dBrKnsutwiOg2hPbvFQ/Image/2011/Thang-6/Tuan-3/hienmaunhandao2_48cbf.JPG\" width=450 _fl=\"\"></div><div align=center><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma; FONT-SIZE: 10pt\">“Mỗi giọt máu cho đi, một cuộc đời ở lại”, hàng ngàn học sinh, sinh viên, công nhân viên chức, lực lượng vũ trang, công nhân... đã chia sẻ những “giọt hồng” quý giá để cứu những người bệnh hiểm nghèo.</span></div><p>“Lúc đầu bố mẹ em không hiểu cứ nghĩ cho máu là mất hoặc sẽ bị thế này thế nọ, có khi còn bảo là ảnh hưởng sức khỏe rồi có thể bị thiếu máu về sau nên ngăn cản và cấm em không được cho máu. Nhưng lần đầu tiên em đã trốn bố mẹ đi hiến máu, sau thấy không ổn, em nhờ mấy chị sinh viên đến phân tích, thuyết phục và em đem cả tờ rơi về cho bố mẹ xem nữa. Giờ thì bố mẹ đã hiểu và cho phép em đi hiến máu. Bố còn nói, nếu công ty phát động, bố cũng sẽ đăng ký hiến máu...”, Trang cười khẽ chia sẻ. </p><div>Trang cho biết, trong hai năm học tại trường, đã 5 lần hiến máu tình nguyện, em còn tích cực tuyên truyền, vận động các bạn trong lớp, trong khoa tham gia hiến máu; là tuyên truyền viên tích cực của CLB hiến máu của trường. Không chỉ tham gia hiến máu theo các đợt vận động của Hội chữ thập đỏ, ở gần các bệnh viện lớn tuyến tỉnh, có những trường hợp cấp cứu cần đến máu, Trung tâm huyết học cần, gọi điện cho Trang, em sẵn lòng đến hiến máu mà không nhận một đồng bồi dưỡng nào. </div><div align=center>&nbsp;</div><div align=center><img style=\"MARGIN: 5px\" align=center src=\"http://dantri4.vcmedia.vn/7dBrKnsutwiOg2hPbvFQ/Image/2011/Thang-6/Tuan-3/hienmau2_78dd3.JPG\" width=450 _fl=\"\"></div><div align=center><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma; FONT-SIZE: 10pt\">SV trường CĐ Việt Nam - Hàn Quốc tham gia hiến máu nhân đạo.</span></div><p>“Cứu người mới là quan trọng. Xem tivi, thấy có bác 50, 60 tuổi, tham gia hiến máu trên dưới 50 lần, em tự hỏi rằng “sao mình trẻ, khỏe lại không hiến máu cứu người”?. Với ý nghĩ đó, để có những giọt máu sạch cứu người, Trang cũng như nhiều bạn sinh viên khác luôn coi trọng chế độ ăn uống, ăn đủ chất, ăn các loại thực phẩm bổ máu, tập thể dục, thể thao đều đặn và sống lành mạnh.</p><p>Theo báo cáo tại Lễ tôn vinh các tập thể, cá nhân có thành tích trong hiến máu tình nguyện trong năm 2010, tỉnh Nghệ An đã tiếp nhận được 6.708 đơn vị máu, trong đó tỷ lệ hiến máu tình nguyện đạt 75% trong tổng số người hiến máu. Có 10.000 cá nhân đăng ký hiến máu tình nguyện. Các hình thức vận động hiến máu ngày càng đa dạng, phong phú, thu hút đông đảo tình nguyện viên tham gia. Đến nay, trên địa bàn tỉnh đã thành lập được 3 CLB hiến máu tình nguyện ở các trường ĐH Vinh, ĐH SPKT Vinh, ĐH Y khoa Vinh. </p><p>Riêng trường ĐH Y khoa Vinh còn thành lập đội “Ngân hàng máu sống” sẵn sàng hiến máu cứu sống những người bệnh trong trường hợp đột xuất mà bệnh viện yêu cầu. Các đơn vị, lực lượng vũ trang cũng vào cuộc tích cực, các đơn vị đã lập danh sách các chiến sỹ có đủ điều kiện sức khỏe tham gia hiến máu; thường xuyên tổ chức các buổi giao lưu văn nghệ, các đợt tuyên truyền về hiến máu cứu người...</p><p>Nói về CLB “ngân hàng máu” TS. Nguyễn Trọng Tài - Hiệu trưởng Trường ĐH Y khoa Vinh cho biết: “Với các em trong câu lạc bộ của trường chúng tôi rất trách nhiệm, nhiều đêm có vấn đề gì khi các vụ tai nạn thiếu máu thì các em sẽ đến và sẵn sàng hiến máu để cứu người. Có những em 7-8 lần hiến máu, việc làm của các em thật vinh dự cho chúng tôi”. </p><div>Bắt đầu từ năm 2008, Ban chỉ đạo hiến máu tình nguyện các cấp được thành lập và đi vào hoạt động có hiệu quả. Điển hình như Ban vận động hiến máu tình nguyện Thị xã Thái Hòa trong năm 2010 đã tiếp nhận 224 đơn vị máu, thành lập được “Ngân hàng máu sống” do Bệnh viện Đa khoa Tây Bắc làm nòng cốt. Đó là Ban vận động hiến máu nhân đạo huyện Quỳnh Lưu, trong năm vận động 600 người đăng ký hiến máu tình nguyện; phối hợp với các bệnh viện trên địa bàn thành lập các đội hiến máu dự bị, mỗi đội có từ 48 đến 100 thành viên, cung cấp lượng máu cấp cứu cho các bệnh viện trên địa bàn...</div><div align=center>&nbsp;</div><div align=center><img style=\"MARGIN: 5px\" align=center src=\"http://dantri4.vcmedia.vn/7dBrKnsutwiOg2hPbvFQ/Image/2011/Thang-6/Tuan-3/hienmau1_b2eac.PNG\" width=450 _fl=\"\"></div><div align=center><span style=\"FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma; FONT-SIZE: 10pt\">Hiến máu cứu người nghĩa cử cao đẹp cần được nhân rộng trong xã hội hiện nay.</span></div><p>Nghệ An là tỉnh thường xuyên gánh chịu hậu quả của thiên tai, địch họa, dịch bệnh, thêm vào đó là tình trạng TNGT ngày càng gia tăng, do đó, nhu cầu máu điều trị ngày càng tăng. Hiện nay, lượng máu thu gom được của cả tỉnh mới chỉ đáp ứng được 60% nhu cầu chữa bệnh. </p><p>Tình trạng thiếu máu vẫn thường xuyên xảy ra, nhất là vào dịp hè, lễ, tết. Do đó, phong trào “hiến máu cứu người” cần được đẩy mạnh, nhân rộng. Những tập thể, cá nhân được tôn vinh lần này là những bông hoa đẹp nhất trong phong trào hiến máu nhân đạo, những trái tim đầy tình nhân ái, đem lại dòng máu hồi sinh cho người bệnh, đại diện cho hàng triệu người hiến máu tình nguyện của Việt Nam.</p><p align=right><span style=\"FONT-WEIGHT: bold\">Thanh Phúc - Tuệ Anh</span></p><input type=\'hidden\' value=\'/c135s135/nhipsongtre/trang-1.htm\' id=\'hidNextUsing\'/>', 12, 66, 0, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(403, 'vi', 'Những điều cấm kị khi bị say nắng', 'Để nhanh chóng làm tan cơn say nắng, đồng thời không gây hại cho sức khỏe, cần lưu ý những điều kiêng kị sau.', 'upload/images/2011-06-14 10-29-57--140611nang_c2c5a.jpg', '2011-06-14', '<div class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"FONT-WEIGHT: bold\"></span>&nbsp;</div><div class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\" align=center><span style=\"FONT-WEIGHT: bold\"><img src=\"hinh/2011-06-14 10-29-57--140611nang_c2c5a.jpg\"><br><br></span></div><div class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"FONT-WEIGHT: bold\">1. Kị uống quá nhiều nước<?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = \"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office\" /><o:p></o:p></span></div><p class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\">Những người bị say nắng, cảm nắng không nên uống liền lúc quá nhiều nước, mà ngược lại phải dùng phương pháp uống ít nước và chia làm nhiều lần, mỗi lần chỉ khoảng 300ml. <o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\">Nguyên nhân là do uống liền lúc quá nhiều nước không những ảnh hưởng đến chức năng tiêu hóa mà còn làm loãng dịch dạ dày, khiến cơ thể ra quá nhiều mồ hôi, từ đó gây mất nước và lượng muối trong cơ thể. Trường hợp nghiêm trọng còn gây chuột rút đường đột. <o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"FONT-WEIGHT: bold\">2. Kiêng kị ăn quá nhiều hoa quả lạnh<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\">Những người thường xuyên bị say nắng khi ra ngoài trời thường bị suy nhược về tì và vị (dạ dày), nếu ăn quá nhiều hoa quả lạnh, những thực phẩm tính hàn dễ làm tổn thương đến dạ dày, gây trướng bụng, tiêu chảy, đau bụng. <o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"FONT-WEIGHT: bold\">3. Kị ăn thực phẩm nhiều dầu mỡ<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\">Sau khi bị cảm nắng, tuyệt đối tránh xa các loại thực phẩm nhiều dầu mỡ, để phần nào giúp cơ thể thích ứng với chức năng tiêu hóa của dạ dày trong mùa hè oi bức. <o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\">Nếu ăn quá nhiều thực phẩm chiên rán nhiều dầu mỡ, dạ dày bị tăng thêm gánh nặng khiến lượng lớn máu của cơ thể dồn đọng ở đường tiêu hóa, lúc đó sẽ thiếu máu để đưa lên não, làm cho cơ thể có cảm giác mệt mỏi hơn, chứng khó tiêu hóa lại thêm trầm trọng. <o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"FONT-WEIGHT: bold\">4. Kị tẩm bổ quá nhiều thực phẩm giàu dinh dưỡng<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\">Sau khi bị say nắng, hơi nóng vẫn chưa hoàn toàn hạ hỏa, lúc này, đừng thấy cơ thể suy yếu mà “tẩm bổ” hết thứ đồ ăn thức uống giàu đạm, nhiều chất béo với mong muốn giúp cơ thể nhanh phục hồi. </p><p class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><div class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\">Việc ăn uống các loại thực phẩm quá giàu chất dinh dưỡng không những chẳng có tác dụng giải cơn say nắng, ngược lại còn kéo dài thêm khí nóng trong người, gây thêm mệt mỏi và hại cho đường tiêu hóa. </div><div class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div><div class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><o:p><div align=center><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=\"90%\" border=1><tbody><tr><td><p><span style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma\">Nắng nóng oi bức khiến cơ thể phải hoạt động hết năng suất để tự điều tiết sao cho thích nghi với điều kiện môi trường. Khi nhiệt độ cơ thể và môi trường quá chênh lệch, cộng thêm sự thích ứng của cơ thể chưa được đáp ứng kịp thời, dễ bị say nắng, biểu hiện nóng sốt, vã mồ hôi, đau đầu, chóng mặt, hoa mắt, thậm chí ngất xỉu. </span></p></td></tr></tbody></table></div></o:p></div><p class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><div class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\" align=right><span style=\"FONT-WEIGHT: bold\"><br>Phạm Hằng<o:p></o:p></span></div><p class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\" align=right>Theo <span style=\"FONT-STYLE: italic\">39net</span><o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><input type=\'hidden\' value=\'/c7s7/suckhoe/trang-1.htm\' id=\'hidNextUsing\'/>', 79, 405, 0, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(405, 'vi', 'Điều tôi muốn biết', 'Tôi không quan tâm bạn mưu sinh thế nào mà chỉ muốn biết bạn khao khát điều gì và có dám mơ ước đạt được điều mình đang khao khát không...Tôi không quan tâm bạn bao nhiêu tuổi mà chỉ muốn biết bạn có dám như một kẻ ngốc liều mình vì tình yêu, vì những ước mơ và vì một chuyến phiêu lưu để được tồn tại trong cuộc đời này không...', 'upload/images/dtmb.jpg', '2011-07-06', '<p>	<font face=\"Verdana, Arial\" size=\"2\">T&ocirc;i kh&ocirc;ng cần biết điều g&igrave; mới ph&ugrave; hợp với ước mơ của bạn m&agrave; chỉ muốn biết bạn đ&atilde; d&aacute;m đối mặt với nỗi đau bị cuộc đời dối tr&aacute; hay lại kh&eacute;p chặt l&ograve;ng m&igrave;nh v&igrave; e sợ lại một nỗi đau kh&aacute;c...<br />	<br />	T&ocirc;i muốn biết bạn c&oacute; d&aacute;m ngồi lại với nỗi đau của t&ocirc;i hay của ch&iacute;nh bạn; c&oacute; d&aacute;m khi&ecirc;u vũ thật đi&ecirc;n cuồng để sự say m&ecirc; tr&agrave;n ngập đến tận đầu ng&oacute;n tay v&agrave; ng&oacute;n ch&acirc;n của m&igrave;nh m&agrave; kh&ocirc;ng cần phải e d&egrave; giữ &yacute;, phải thực tế hay phải lu&ocirc;n nhớ đến những giới hạn của con người...<br />	<br />	T&ocirc;i kh&ocirc;ng quan t&acirc;m c&acirc;u chuyện bạn kể c&oacute; thật hay kh&ocirc;ng m&agrave; chỉ muốn biết bạn c&oacute; d&aacute;m l&agrave;m thất vọng người kh&aacute;c để th&agrave;nh thật với bản th&acirc;n m&igrave;nh... Liệu bạn c&oacute; thể chịu đựng bị kết tội phản bội m&agrave; vẫn kh&ocirc;ng phản bội lại ch&iacute;nh nh&acirc;n c&aacute;ch của m&igrave;nh... Liệu bạn sẽ trung thực v&agrave; v&igrave; thế sẽ đ&aacute;ng được tin cậy chứ...<br />	<br />	T&ocirc;i muốn biết liệu bạn c&oacute; nhận ra vẻ đẹp d&ugrave; cho hằng ng&agrave;y n&oacute; chẳng hề xinh đẹp, v&agrave; liệu bạn c&oacute; thể quyết định cuộc đời m&igrave;nh m&agrave; kh&ocirc;ng cần sự hiện diện của Ch&uacute;a...<br />	<br />	T&ocirc;i muốn biết liệu bạn sẽ chịu đựng được thất bại của lẫn bạn v&agrave; t&ocirc;i, đứng b&ecirc;n bờ hồ m&agrave; h&eacute;t vang đến tận trời cao l&agrave; &ldquo;c&oacute;&rdquo;...<br />	<br />	T&ocirc;i muốn biết liệu bạn c&oacute; thể thức dậy d&ugrave; sau đ&ecirc;m d&agrave;i đau khổ, thất vọng, kiệt sức v&agrave; r&atilde; rời m&agrave; l&agrave;m những g&igrave; phải l&agrave;m cho c&aacute;c con của bạn kh&ocirc;ng...<br />	<br />	T&ocirc;i kh&ocirc;ng quan t&acirc;m bạn l&agrave; ai hay l&agrave;m sao đến được đ&acirc;y. T&ocirc;i chỉ muốn biết liệu bạn c&oacute; thể s&aacute;t c&aacute;nh c&ugrave;ng t&ocirc;i trong lửa đỏ v&agrave; sẽ kh&ocirc;ng ch&ugrave;n bước tho&aacute;i lui...<br />	<br />	T&ocirc;i kh&ocirc;ng quan t&acirc;m bạn đ&atilde; học ở đ&acirc;u, những g&igrave; v&agrave; của ai. T&ocirc;i chỉ muốn biết liệu bạn c&oacute; thể một m&igrave;nh đối diện với bản th&acirc;n ch&acirc;n thật như người bạn bạn c&oacute; b&ecirc;n m&igrave;nh trong những gi&acirc;y ph&uacute;t đơn độc...</font></p>', 12, 419, 0, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(406, 'vi', 'Phật ở đâu?', 'Thuở xưa, có anh chàng đọc kinh nghe nói về Phật, thích lắm, quyết định đi tìm gặp Ngài bằng được. Anh chàng khăn gói quả mướp ra đi. Sau khi trải qua không biết cơ man nào là núi sông, thành phố, hầm hố gian nguy hiểm trở... Chàng vẫn chưa gặp được Phật giống như hình dạng trong Kinh đã diễn tả.', '', '2011-06-14', '<p>	<font face=\"Verdana, Arial\" size=\"2\">&quot;Th&acirc;n Phật sắc v&agrave;ng, cao một trượng s&aacute;u, đầy đủ ba mươi hai tướng tốt, t&aacute;m mươi vẻ đẹp, h&agrave;o quang ch&oacute;i s&aacute;ng. &quot;<br />	<br />	Một h&ocirc;m tại một sườn non, ch&agrave;ng trai t&igrave;nh cờ gặp một cụ gi&agrave; r&acirc;u t&oacute;c bạc phơ, cốt c&aacute;ch si&ecirc;u ph&agrave;m, mừng qu&aacute;, ch&agrave;ng khẩn khoản:<br />	<br />	- Thưa cụ, cụ c&oacute; biết Phật đang ngụ ở đ&acirc;u kh&ocirc;ng... Xin chỉ d&ugrave;m cho con với.<br />	<br />	&Ocirc;ng l&atilde;o mĩm cười:<br />	<br />	- Ồ! Chỗ n&agrave;o m&agrave; kh&ocirc;ng c&oacute; Phật... Tr&ecirc;n qu&atilde;ng đường vừa qua, chả lẽ con kh&ocirc;ng gặp được Ng&agrave;i ư...<br />	<br />	- Thưa cụ, tr&ecirc;n đường đi con đ&atilde; từng gặp v&ocirc; số người, nhưng đều l&agrave; hạng ph&agrave;m phu tục tử cả. Con chưa từng thấy người n&agrave;o c&oacute; được v&agrave;i tướng tốt như trong kinh đ&atilde; m&ocirc; tả về Phật cả.<br />	<br />	&Ocirc;ng cụ cười ha hả:<br />	<br />	- Ch&aacute;u ngốc nghếch thật, ch&aacute;u kh&ocirc;ng biết rằng c&aacute;i th&acirc;n đầy đủ ba mươi hai tướng tốt v&agrave; t&aacute;m mươi vẻ đẹp đ&oacute; người Ấn Độ đ&atilde; đốt th&agrave;nh tro v&agrave; chia nhau x&acirc;y th&aacute;p thờ c&uacute;ng cả rồi ư...<br />	<br />	- Thưa, thế th&igrave; Phật chết rồi sao...<br />	<br />	- Hiện giờ Đức Phật đang ph&acirc;n th&acirc;n ở khắp mọi nơi. Ng&agrave;i cũng mang th&acirc;n tốt v&agrave; xấu như ch&uacute;ng sinh vậy. Con c&oacute; c&ograve;n muốn gặp Ng&agrave;i nữa kh&ocirc;ng...<br />	<br />	- Thưa, d&ugrave; bất cứ với h&igrave;nh d&aacute;ng n&agrave;o, nếu đ&iacute;ch thật l&agrave; Ng&agrave;i th&igrave; con vẫn v&ocirc; c&ugrave;ng kh&aacute;t ngưỡng.<br />	<br />	- Vậy th&igrave;, để ta m&aacute;ch nước cho con nh&eacute;... Con h&atilde;y quay về, tr&ecirc;n đường về nếu con gặp người n&agrave;o mang guốc tr&aacute;i ở ch&acirc;n phải, guốc phải ở ch&acirc;n tr&aacute;i th&igrave; người đ&oacute; ch&iacute;nh l&agrave; một h&oacute;a th&acirc;n của Phật. H&atilde;y thừa sự v&agrave; c&uacute;ng dường vị Phật ấy như trong kinh đ&atilde; dạy.<br />	<br />	Ch&agrave;ng trai hối hả quay về. Suốt qu&atilde;ng đường d&agrave;i, ch&agrave;ng kh&ocirc;ng gặp Đức Phật n&agrave;o m&agrave; h&igrave;nh dạng như cụ gi&agrave; diễn tả. Ch&aacute;n nản, ch&agrave;ng đi lu&ocirc;n về nh&agrave;. Trời đ&atilde; khuya, b&agrave; mẹ c&ograve;n chong đ&egrave;n ngồi đợi con. Nghe tiếng gọi cửa b&agrave; mừng qu&aacute;, quờ quạng t&igrave;m đ&ocirc;i guốc rồi chống gậy tất tả ra mở cửa.<br />	<br />	Ch&agrave;ng trai thấy mẹ tiều tụy, nước mắt chảy d&agrave;i tr&ecirc;n đ&ocirc;i m&aacute; nhăn nheo, mang lộn chiếc guốc tr&aacute;i qua ch&acirc;n phải, guốc phải sang ch&acirc;n tr&aacute;i. Ch&agrave;ng &ocirc;m chầm lấy mẹ nghẹn ng&agrave;o: &quot;&Ocirc;i Đức Phật y&ecirc;u qu&iacute; của con. &quot;</font></p>', 12, 115, 0, 1, '', NULL, NULL),
(407, 'vi', 'Món quà năm mới', 'Một ngày nọ, hai cậu bé đang chơi đùa thì một bà tiên xuất hiện trước mặt và nói: \"Ta tặng cho các cháu món quà năm mới\". Bà trao cho mỗi đứa một gói quà và biến mất.', 'upload/images/qua.jpg', '2011-07-06', '<p>	<font face=\"Verdana, Arial\" size=\"2\">Carl v&agrave; Philip mở những g&oacute;i qu&agrave; ra v&agrave; thấy trong đ&oacute; l&agrave; những quyển s&aacute;ch xinh đẹp, những trang giấy trắng tinh như tuyết khi lật trang đầu ti&ecirc;n.<br />	<br />	Nhiều th&aacute;ng tr&ocirc;i qua, b&agrave; ti&ecirc;n lại đến v&agrave; n&oacute;i &ldquo;Ta đ&atilde; cho c&aacute;c ch&aacute;u mỗi đứa một quyển s&aacute;ch, b&acirc;y giờ ta sẽ mang về lại để trả cho Thần Thời Gian, đ&oacute; l&agrave; người đ&atilde; gởi những quyển s&aacute;ch n&agrave;y đến cho c&aacute;c ch&aacute;u&rdquo;<br />	<br />	&ldquo;Ch&aacute;u kh&ocirc;ng thể giữ quyển s&aacute;ch n&agrave;y l&acirc;u hơn một ch&uacute;t sao? Philip hỏi. &ldquo;Ch&aacute;u sẽ kh&oacute; nhớ đến n&oacute; sau n&agrave;y. Ch&aacute;u muốn vẽ một c&aacute;i g&igrave; đ&oacute; l&ecirc;n trang cuối c&ugrave;ng.<br />	<br />	&ldquo;Kh&ocirc;ng, &rdquo; b&agrave; ti&ecirc;n n&oacute;i, &ldquo;Ta phải lấy n&oacute; đi với nguy&ecirc;n trạng như thế.<br />	<br />	&ldquo;Ch&aacute;u ước g&igrave; ch&aacute;u c&oacute; thể nh&igrave;n hết cuốn của ch&aacute;u một lần&rdquo; Carl n&oacute;i, &ldquo;Ch&aacute;u chỉ được xem mỗi lần c&oacute; một trang, bởi v&igrave; khi tờ giấy lật qua n&oacute; d&iacute;nh chặt thật nhanh v&agrave; ch&aacute;u kh&ocirc;ng thể n&agrave;o mở hơn một trang mỗi ng&agrave;y&rdquo;.<br />	<br />	&ldquo;C&aacute;c ch&aacute;u h&atilde;y nh&igrave;n lại quyển s&aacute;ch của m&igrave;nh đi&rdquo; b&agrave; ti&ecirc;n đ&aacute;p v&agrave; thắp cho ch&uacute;ng hai ngọn đ&egrave;n nhỏ, bằng &aacute;nh s&aacute;ng ấy ch&uacute;ng đ&atilde; xem được những trang s&aacute;ch khi b&agrave; ti&ecirc;n lật qua.<br />	<br />	Những cậu b&eacute; xem v&agrave; ngạc nhi&ecirc;n tự hỏi, đ&acirc;y c&oacute; phải ch&iacute;nh l&agrave; cuốn s&aacute;ch đẹp m&agrave; b&agrave; đ&atilde; cho ch&uacute;ng c&aacute;ch đ&acirc;y một năm kh&ocirc;ng? Nơi những trang sạch sẽ trắng tinh v&agrave; đẹp như tuyết khi lần đầu ti&ecirc;n ch&uacute;ng lật ra giờ đ&acirc;y lại l&agrave; một trang với những vết hoen ố xấu x&iacute; v&agrave; vết c&agrave;o xước tr&ecirc;n đ&oacute;; trong khi ch&iacute;nh trang kế tiếp lại c&oacute; một bức tranh nhỏ nhắn đ&aacute;ng y&ecirc;u. Một v&agrave;i trang được trang tr&iacute; với những m&agrave;u sắc &oacute;ng &aacute;nh lộng lẫy, những trang kh&aacute;c l&agrave; những b&ocirc;ng hoa xinh đẹp. V&agrave; c&ograve;n c&oacute; những trang với một chiếc cầu vồng rực s&aacute;ng trang nh&atilde;. Tuy nhi&ecirc;n ngay cả tr&ecirc;n những trang đẹp đẽ nhất cũng c&oacute; những vết hoen v&agrave; vết c&agrave;o xước xấu x&iacute;.<br />	<br />	Cuối c&ugrave;ng Carl v&agrave; Philip ngước l&ecirc;n nh&igrave;n b&agrave; ti&ecirc;n<br />	<br />	&ldquo;Ai đ&atilde; l&agrave;m như thế n&agrave;y? &rdquo; Ch&uacute;ng c&ugrave;ng hỏi. &ldquo;Mỗi trang đều trắng v&agrave; đẹp khi ch&uacute;ng ch&aacute;u lật ra; nhưng giờ đ&acirc;y th&igrave; kh&ocirc;ng c&ograve;n một trang trắng n&agrave;o trong to&agrave;n bộ quyển s&aacute;ch&rdquo;<br />	<br />	&ldquo;Ta sẽ giảng giải những bức tranh cho c&aacute;c ch&aacute;u&rdquo; b&agrave; ti&ecirc;n n&oacute;i v&agrave; mỉm cười nh&igrave;n hai đứa.<br />	<br />	&ldquo;Xem n&agrave;o Philip, những ch&ugrave;m hoa hồng tươi tắn tr&ecirc;n trang n&agrave;y l&agrave; khi ch&aacute;u để cho em b&eacute; chơi đồ chơi của ch&aacute;u; v&agrave; con chim xinh đẹp n&agrave;y, n&oacute; tr&ocirc;ng như thể đang h&oacute;t bằng tất cả tr&aacute;i tim, sẽ kh&ocirc;ng bao giờ xuất hiện tr&ecirc;n trang n&agrave;y nếu ch&aacute;u kh&ocirc;ng cố ngoan ngo&atilde;n v&agrave; vui vẻ trong ng&agrave;y m&agrave; thay v&agrave;o đ&oacute; l&agrave; c&atilde;i cọ, c&agrave;u nh&agrave;u&rdquo;<br />	<br />	&ldquo;Nhưng c&aacute;i g&igrave; đ&atilde; l&agrave;m những vết đốm như thế n&agrave;y? Philip hỏi.<br />	<br />	&ldquo;&ETH;iều đ&oacute; đ&atilde; xảy ra khi một ng&agrave;y n&agrave;o đ&oacute; ch&aacute;u n&oacute;i một điều giả dối, v&agrave; đ&acirc;y l&agrave; khi ch&aacute;u kh&ocirc;ng quan t&acirc;m nghe lời mẹ. Tất cả những vết hoen v&agrave; vết trầy xước tr&ocirc;ng rất xấu x&iacute;, đều c&ugrave;ng c&oacute; trong s&aacute;ch của ch&aacute;u v&agrave; Carl, được h&igrave;nh th&agrave;nh khi c&aacute;c ch&aacute;u qu&aacute; nghịch ngợm. Mỗi điều xinh đẹp trong quyển s&aacute;ch n&agrave;y sẽ đến khi c&aacute;c ch&aacute;u l&agrave;m điều tốt đẹp&rdquo;<br />	<br />	&ldquo;O&agrave;, gi&aacute; m&agrave; ch&uacute;ng ch&aacute;u c&oacute; thể c&oacute; lại cuốn s&aacute;ch lần nữa&rdquo; Carl v&agrave; Philip c&ugrave;ng n&oacute;i<br />	<br />	&ldquo;&ETH;iều đ&oacute; th&igrave; kh&ocirc;ng thể được&rdquo; b&agrave; ti&ecirc;n đ&aacute;p &rdquo; H&atilde;y nh&igrave;n xem! Những quyển s&aacute;ch n&agrave;y đ&atilde; được ghi ng&agrave;y th&aacute;ng cho mỗi năm. V&agrave; b&acirc;y giờ ch&uacute;ng phải trở về hộp s&aacute;ch của Thần Thời Gian, nhưng ta sẽ mang đến cho c&aacute;c ch&aacute;u một quyển s&aacute;ch mới. C&oacute; lẽ c&aacute;c ch&aacute;u c&oacute; thể l&agrave;m cho những cuốn s&aacute;ch n&agrave;y tươi đẹp hơn nhưng cuốn kia&rdquo;<br />	<br />	N&oacute;i xong b&agrave; ti&ecirc;n biến mất, nhưng trong tay mỗi cậu b&eacute; l&agrave; một quyển s&aacute;ch mới được mở ở trang đầu ti&ecirc;n. Tr&ecirc;n g&aacute;y s&aacute;ch ghi d&ograve;ng chữ m&agrave;u v&agrave;ng: &ldquo;D&agrave;nh cho Năm Mới&rdquo;</font><br />	&nbsp;</p><div class=\"small\">	<font face=\"Verdana, Arial\" size=\"2\">Nhị Tường dịch</font></div>', 12, 319, 0, 1, 'Việt Nam', NULL, NULL);
